0,Lactuca virosa L.,Lactuca virosa,Lactuca,Asteraceae,virosa,L.,,DD,3140346,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Lactuca virosa,https://www.gbif.org/species/3140346,Acrid lettuce; Bitter lettuce; Great Lettuce; Greater Lettuce; Greater Prickly Lettuce; wild lettuce,"Annual to biennial, up to 200 cm high. Root fusiform, branched, foetid. Stem erect, glabrou.s or setose below. Leaves broad, non-lobed, ovate-oblong in outline (var. virosa), or pinnatifid to pinnatisect with broad, backwards curved lobes( var. cruenta). All with blunt apex and sagittate base green or violet tinged, spinolis-ciliate on the midrib and sometimes also on the lateral nerves beneath. Inflorescence a long, pyramidal panicle. Bracts ovate, with appressed rounded auricles. Heads numerous, 10 mm in diameter, composed of c. 15 florets. Involucral bracts ovate, 10-12 mm long, glabrous. Ligules pale yellow. Achenes broadly elliptical, 6-10 mm long, narrowly winged, rugose but not spiculate or setose, 5-ribbed, blackish. Beak filiform, white, as long as body. Pappus white. 2n = 18.\r\rfrom: Feráková, V. 1977: The Genus Lactuca in Europe – Bratislava.",Cichorieae Systematics Portal,eng,North America (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Algeria; Austria; Baleares; Belgium; California (INTRODUCED); Chile Central (INTRODUCED); Corse; Czechia-Slovakia; District of Columbia (INTRODUCED); France; Germany; Great Britain; Greece; Hungary; Italy; Madeira; Morocco; NW. Balkan Pen.,habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial,Lactuca virosa,"Lactuca virosa is a plant in the Lactuca (lettuce) genus, often ingested for its mild analgesic and sedative effects. It is related to common lettuce, and is often called wild lettuce, bitter lettuce, laitue vireuse, opium lettuce, poisonous lettuce, tall lettuce, great lettuce or rakutu-karyumu-so.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lactuca_virosa,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Lactuca+virosa,"Annual to biennial, up to 200 cm high. Root fusiform, branched, foetid. Stem erect, glabrou.s or setose below. Leaves broad, non-lobed, ovate-oblong in outline (var. virosa), or pinnatifid to pinnatisect with broad, backwards curved lobes( var. cruenta). All with blunt apex and sagittate base green or violet tinged, spinolis-ciliate on the midrib and sometimes also on the lateral nerves beneath. Inflorescence a long, pyramidal panicle. Bracts ovate, with appressed rounded auricles. Heads numerous, 10 mm in diameter, composed of c. 15 florets. Involucral bracts ovate, 10-12 mm long, glabrous. Ligules pale yellow. Achenes broadly elliptical, 6-10 mm long, narrowly winged, rugose but not spiculate or setose, 5-ribbed, blackish. Beak filiform, white, as long as body. Pappus white. 2n = 18.\r\rfrom: Feráková, V. 1977: The Genus Lactuca in Europe – Bratislava.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 0
Scientific name: Lactuca virosa
Full species name: Lactuca virosa L.
Genus: Lactuca
Family: Asteraceae
IUCN status: DD
Accepted scientific name: Lactuca virosa
Common names: Acrid lettuce; Bitter lettuce; Great Lettuce; Greater Lettuce; Greater Prickly Lettuce; wild lettuce
GBIF description: Annual to biennial, up to 200 cm high. Root fusiform, branched, foetid. Stem erect, glabrou.s or setose below. Leaves broad, non-lobed, ovate-oblong in outline (var. virosa), or pinnatifid to pinnatisect with broad, backwards curved lobes( var. cruenta). All with blunt apex and sagittate base green or violet tinged, spinolis-ciliate on the midrib and sometimes also on the lateral nerves beneath. Inflorescence a long, pyramidal panicle. Bracts ovate, with appressed rounded auricles. Heads numerous, 10 mm in diameter, composed of c. 15 florets. Involucral bracts ovate, 10-12 mm long, glabrous. Ligules pale yellow. Achenes broadly elliptical, 6-10 mm long, narrowly winged, rugose but not spiculate or setose, 5-ribbed, blackish. Beak filiform, white, as long as body. Pappus white. 2n = 18.\r\rfrom: Feráková, V. 1977: The Genus Lactuca in Europe – Bratislava.
Wikipedia summary: Lactuca virosa is a plant in the Lactuca (lettuce) genus, often ingested for its mild analgesic and sedative effects. It is related to common lettuce, and is often called wild lettuce, bitter lettuce, laitue vireuse, opium lettuce, poisonous lettuce, tall lettuce, great lettuce or rakutu-karyumu-so.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Algeria; Austria; Baleares; Belgium; California (INTRODUCED); Chile Central (INTRODUCED); Corse; Czechia-Slovakia; District of Columbia (INTRODUCED); France; Germany; Great Britain; Greece; Hungary; Italy; Madeira; Morocco; NW. Balkan Pen.
Profile: habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial
Sources: https://www.gbif.org/species/3140346 | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lactuca_virosa | https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Lactuca+virosa",ok
