6,Pelargonium peltatum (L.) L'Hér.,Pelargonium peltatum,Pelargonium,Geraniaceae,peltatum,(L.) L'Hér.,,Not assessed,9561762,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Pelargonium peltatum,https://www.gbif.org/species/9561762,hanging geranium; ivy geranium; ivy-leaf pelargonium; Ivyleaf Geranium,Nativa de Sudáfrica | cultivada en climas templados,"Especies introducidas, exóticas, trasplantadas, invasoras y potencialmente invasoras obtenidas a partir de fuentes primarias y secundarias, incorporadas en el diagnóstico del Plan Nacional de Prevención, Control y Manejo",,"Caribbean (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); California (INTRODUCED); Canary Is. (INTRODUCED); Cape Provinces; Ecuador (INTRODUCED); Mexico Southwest (INTRODUCED); Morocco (INTRODUCED); Puerto Rico (INTRODUCED); Spain [c]; France [I]; Italy [I]; Croatia [I]; Greece [I]; Morocco [c]; Azores [I] (Sao Miguel Isl. [I]); Canary Isl. [I] (Gran Canaria [I]); South Africa (W-Cape Prov., E-Cape Prov.); Mauritius [I]; La Réunion [I]; Turkey [I]; India [c]; New Zealand [I]; USA [I] (California [I]); Mexico [I]; Honduras [I]; Puerto Rico [I]; Colombia [I]; Venezuela [I]; Ecuador [I]; Manizales; BR (MANAGED); Juan Fernandez Islands (PRESENT); Cundinamarca (MANAGED); HR (PRESENT); LY (PRESENT); São Miguel Island (RARE); SE (IRREGULAR); conterminous 48 United States (PRESENT); ZA (NATIVE)","habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Subarbusto""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}; lifeForm: Hierba; lifeForm: Hierba",Pelargonium peltatum,"Pelargonium peltatum is a scrambling purple perennial plant with five shallow or deeply lobed, circular- to heart-shaped, somewhat fleshy leaves, sometimes with a differently coloured semicircular band, that has been assigned to the cranesbill family. It carries umbel-like inflorescences with 2–10, white to mauve, bilateral symmetrical flowers, each with a ""spur"" that is merged with the flower stalk. It is known by several c