Wikipedia summary: Tradescantia fluminensis is a species of spiderwort native to South America. It is one of several plants known by the common name wandering Jew. It is also known as small-leaf spiderwort, river spiderwort, inch plant, speedy Henry, wandering willie and wandering trad.
Distribution: Galápagos Islands (PRESENT); Tristan da Cunha (PRESENT); Bogotá (INTRODUCED); Africa (PRESENT); Australia (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); South America (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northeast; Argentina Northwest; Azores (INTRODUCED); Baleares (INTRODUCED); Bolivia (INTRODUCED); Brazil Southeast; Brazil South; California (INTRODUCED); Canary Is. (INTRODUCED); Cape Provinces (INTRODUCED); China South-Central (INTRODUCED)
