Wikipedia summary: Tradescantia zebrina, formerly known as Zebrina pendula, is a species of creeping plant in the Tradescantia genus. Common names include silver inch plant and wandering Jew. The latter name is controversial, and some now use the alternative wandering dude. The plant is popular in cultivation due to its fast growth and attractive foliage. It is used as a groundcover in warm winter climates, and as a houseplant elsewhere.
Distribution: East Africa (PRESENT); Galápagos Islands (PRESENT); Área Natural Única Los Estoraques; Complejo Humedales Hato Corozal. Cienaga Zapatosa; Bogotá (INTRODUCED); Jardín Botánico de Bogotá; Caribbean (PRESENT); Middle America (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); South America (PRESENT); Algeria (INTRODUCED); Angola (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh (INTRODUCED); Belize; Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Bolivia (INTRODUCED); Brazil Northeast (INTRODUCED)
