Wikipedia summary: Dryopteris filix-mas, the male fern, is a common fern of the temperate Northern Hemisphere, native to much of Europe, Asia, and North America. It favours damp shaded areas in the understory of woodlands, but also shady places on hedge-banks, and rocks, and screes. Near the northern limit of its distribution it prefers sunny, well-drained sites. It is much less abundant in North America than in Europe.
Distribution: Beitstad; North America (PRESENT); Afghanistan; Albania; Alberta; Algeria; Altay; Argentina South (INTRODUCED); Arizona; Austria; Baleares; Baltic States; Belarus; Belgium; British Columbia; Bulgaria; Buryatiya; California; Central European Russia; Chatham Is. (INTRODUCED)
