40,Helminthotheca echioides (L.) Holub,Helminthotheca echioides,Helminthotheca,Asteraceae,echioides,(L.) Holub,,Not assessed,3141855,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Helminthotheca echioides,https://www.gbif.org/species/3141855,Bristly Oxtongue; Ox Tongue; Ox-tongue; Oxtongue,"Herb, biennial, pauciennial or annual, (5)-10-80-(100) cm high, hispid. Flowering stems erect, ribbed, unbranched or branched. Lower cauline leaves obovate to elliptic, 4.0-12.0 cm long, 1.0-2.0 cm wide, entire or dentate, obtuse or acute, petiole-like attenuate. Middle and upper cauline leaves ovate to elliptic, acute, semiamplexicaul with shortly projecting auricles. Synflorescence corymbiform. Peduncle 1.0-5.0 cm long. Involucre at flowering broadly campanulate, 10.0-18.0 mm long, at flowering 8.0-15.0 mm in diameter; outer involucral bracts ovate, 10.0-18.0 mm long, (3.0)-6.0-10.0 mm wide, acuminate, hispid at margins and midrib; inner involucral bracts linear, 10.0-18.0 mm long, 2.0-3.5 mm wide, hispid at midrib, margin scarious. Receptacle flat, pitted, without scales. Corolla ligulate, yellow; tube c. 6.0 mm long, glabrous below and pilose at apex; ligule c. 7.0 mm long, 0.8 mm wide, tinged purple. Anthertube c. 2.0 mm long; apical appendages obtuse. Style c. 10.0 mm long, greenish; branches c. 1.0 mm long. Achenes dimorphic, the outer achenes a little longer than the inner ones, with a shorter pappus, all narrowly obovoid or cylindrical in outline, compressed, (2.0)-3.0-3.5 mm long, 1.0-1.5 mm wide, glabrous, transversely wrinkled, light brown, with a filiform beak; beak 5.0-6.0 mm long. Pappus white, (4.5)-6.0-7.0 mm long, plumose.\r\rBased on: Meikle, R.D. 1985: Flora auf Cyprus 2. – Kew; Sell, P. and Murell, G. 2006: Flora of Great Britain and Ireland 4. – Cambridge; Tadesse, M. 2004: 27. Helminthotheca - Pp. 71 in: Hedberg, I., Friis, I., Edwards, S. Flora of Ethiopia and Eritrea. – Uppsala.",Cichorieae Systematics Portal,eng,North America (PRESENT); Albania; Alberta (INTRODUCED); Algeria; Arizona (INTRODUCED); Austria (INTRODUCED); Azores; Baleares; Baltic States (INTRODUCED); Belarus (INTRODUCED); Belgium (INTRODUCED); Bulgaria; California (INTRODUCED); Canary Is.; Cape Provinces (INTRODUCED); Cape Verde; Central European Russia (INTRODUCED); Chatham Is. (INTRODUCED); Connecticut (INTRODUCED); Corse,habitat: Freshwater; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial,Helminthotheca echioides,"Helminthotheca echioides, known as bristly oxtongue, is a sprawling annual or biennial herb native to Europe and North Africa. It was originally placed within the genus Picris but is often separated within the small genus Helminthotheca alongside a few other plants which also have the distinctive outer row of bracts around the flowerheads. It is a ruderal plant, found on waste ground and agricultural soils around the world, and in some places it is considered a troublesome weed.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helminthotheca_echioides,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Helminthotheca+echioides,"Herb, biennial, pauciennial or annual, (5)-10-80-(100) cm high, hispid. Flowering stems erect, ribbed, unbranched or branched. Lower cauline leaves obovate to elliptic, 4.0-12.0 cm long, 1.0-2.0 cm wide, entire or dentate, obtuse or acute, petiole-like attenuate. Middle and upper cauline leaves ovate to elliptic, acute, semiamplexicaul with shortly projecting auricles. Synflorescence corymbiform. Peduncle 1.0-5.0 cm long. Involucre at flowering broadly campanulate, 10.0-18.0 mm long, at flowering 8.0-15.0 mm in diameter; outer involucral bracts ovate, 10.0-18.0 mm long, (3.0)-6.0-10.0 mm wide, acuminate, hispid at margins and midrib; inner involucral bracts linear, 10.0-18.0 mm long, 2.0-3.5 mm wide, hispid at midrib, margin scarious. Receptacle flat, pitted, without scales. Corolla ligulate, yellow; tube c. 6.0 mm long, glabrous below and pilose at apex; ligule c. 7.0 mm long, 0.8 mm wide, tinged purple. Anthertube c. 2.0 mm long; apical appendages obtuse. Style c. 10.0 mm long, greenish; branches c. 1.0 mm long. Achenes dimorphic, the outer achenes a little longer than the inner ones, with a shorter pappus, all narrowly obovoid or cylindrical in outline, compressed, (2.0)-3.0-3.5 mm long, 1.0-1.5 mm wide, glabrous, transversely wrinkled, light brown, with a filiform beak; beak 5.0-6.0 mm long. Pappus white, (4.5)-6.0-7.0 mm long, plumose.\r\rBased on: Meikle, R.D. 1985: Flora auf Cyprus 2. – Kew; Sell, P. and Murell, G. 2006: Flora of Great Britain and Ireland 4. – Cambridge; Tadesse, M. 2004: 27. Helminthotheca - Pp. 71 in: Hedberg, I., Friis, I., Edwards, S. Flora of Ethiopia and Eritrea. – Uppsala.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 40
Scientific name: Helminthotheca echioides
Full species name: Helminthotheca echioides (L.) Holub
Genus: Helminthotheca
Family: Asteraceae
IUCN status: Not assessed
Accepted scientific name: Helminthotheca echioides
Common names: Bristly Oxtongue; Ox Tongue; Ox-tongue; Oxtongue
GBIF description: Herb, biennial, pauciennial or annual, (5)-10-80-(100) cm high, hispid. Flowering stems erect, ribbed, unbranched or branched. Lower cauline leaves obovate to elliptic, 4.0-12.0 cm long, 1.0-2.0 cm wide, entire or dentate, obtuse or acute, petiole-like attenuate. Middle and upper cauline leaves ovate to elliptic, acute, semiamplexicaul with shortly projecting auricles. Synflorescence corymbiform. Peduncle 1.0-5.0 cm long. Involucre at flowering broadly campanulate, 10.0-18.0 mm long, at flowering 8.0-15.0 mm in diameter; outer involucral bracts ovate, 10.0-18.0 mm long, (3.0)-6.0-10.0 mm wide, acuminate, hispid at margins and midrib; inner involucral bracts linear, 10.0-18.0 mm long, 2.0-3.5 mm wide, hispid at midrib, margin scarious. Receptacle flat, pitted, without scales. Corolla ligulate, yellow; tube c. 6.0 mm long, glabrous below and pilose at apex; ligule c. 7.0 mm long, 0.8 mm wide, tinged purple. Anthertube c. 2.0 mm long; apical appendages obtuse. Style c. 10.0 mm long, greenish; branches c. 1.0 mm long. Achenes dimorphic, the outer achenes a little longer than the inner ones, with a shorter pappus, all narrowly obovoid or cylindrical in outline, compressed, (2.0)-3.0-3.5 mm long, 1.0-1.5 mm wide, glabrous, transversely wrinkled, light brown, with a filiform beak; beak 5.0-6.0 mm long. Pappus white, (4.5)-6.0-7.0 mm long, plumose.\r\rBased on: Meikle, R.D. 1985: Flora auf Cyprus 2. – Kew; Sell, P. and Murell, G. 2006: Flora of Great Britain and Ireland 4. – Cambridge; Tadesse, M. 2004: 27. Helminthotheca - Pp. 71 in: Hedberg, I., Friis, I., Edwards, S. Flora of Ethiopia and Eritrea. – Uppsala.
Wikipedia summary: Helminthotheca echioides, known as bristly oxtongue, is a sprawling annual or biennial herb native to Europe and North Africa. It was originally placed within the genus Picris but is often separated within the small genus Helminthotheca alongside a few other plants which also have the distinctive outer row of bracts around the flowerheads. It is a ruderal plant, found on waste ground and agricultural soils around the world, and in some places it is considered a troublesome weed.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Albania; Alberta (INTRODUCED); Algeria; Arizona (INTRODUCED); Austria (INTRODUCED); Azores; Baleares; Baltic States (INTRODUCED); Belarus (INTRODUCED); Belgium (INTRODUCED); Bulgaria; California (INTRODUCED); Canary Is.; Cape Provinces (INTRODUCED); Cape Verde; Central European Russia (INTRODUCED); Chatham Is. (INTRODUCED); Connecticut (INTRODUCED); Corse
Profile: habitat: Freshwater; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial
