Wikipedia summary: Alliaria petiolata, or garlic mustard, is a biennial flowering plant in the mustard family (Brassicaceae). It is native to Europe, western and central Asia, north-western Africa, Morocco, Iberia and the British Isles, north to northern Scandinavia, and east to northern Pakistan and Xinjiang in western China. It has now become a tenacious invasive plant across the northern U.S., in particular because of its earlier springtime emergence than many native species, often in the forest understory.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Afghanistan; Alabama (INTRODUCED); Albania; Algeria; Argentina South (INTRODUCED); Austria; Baltic States; Belarus; Belgium; British Columbia (INTRODUCED); Bulgaria; Central European Russia; Colorado (INTRODUCED); Connecticut (INTRODUCED); Corse; Cyprus; Czechia-Slovakia; Delaware (INTRODUCED); Denmark
