105,Trifolium lappaceum L.,Trifolium lappaceum,Trifolium,Fabaceae,lappaceum,L.,,Not assessed,5358913,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Trifolium lappaceum,https://www.gbif.org/species/5358913,Bur Clover; Burdock clover; lappa clover,"Note: Many authors have followed Zohary (in Candollea 27: 144. 1972) in treating 930.28 (LINN) as the type. However, this sheet is not annotated in a way to link it to this name, and is indeed the lectotype of another species, T. alpestre L. Although it is possible that Zohary cited sheet 930.28 in error for 930.23 (apparently original material for this name), this cannot be safely assumed, and the name remains at present untypified.",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part T),eng,North America (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Albania; Algeria; Azores; Baleares; Belgium (INTRODUCED); Bulgaria; Canary Is.; Corse; Cyprus; Czechia-Slovakia (INTRODUCED); East Aegean Is.; Florida (INTRODUCED); France; Georgia (INTRODUCED); Germany (INTRODUCED); Greece; Gulf States; Iran,habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial,Trifolium lappaceum,"Trifolium lappaceum, the burdock clover, is a species of annual herb in the family Fabaceae. They have a self-supporting growth form and compound, broad leaves.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trifolium_lappaceum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Trifolium+lappaceum,"Note: Many authors have followed Zohary (in Candollea 27: 144. 1972) in treating 930.28 (LINN) as the type. However, this sheet is not annotated in a way to link it to this name, and is indeed the lectotype of another species, T. alpestre L. Although it is possible that Zohary cited sheet 930.28 in error for 930.23 (apparently original material for this name), this cannot be safely assumed, and the name remains at present untypified.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 105
Scientific name: Trifolium lappaceum
Full species name: Trifolium lappaceum L.
Genus: Trifolium
Family: Fabaceae
IUCN status: Not assessed
Accepted scientific name: Trifolium lappaceum
Common names: Bur Clover; Burdock clover; lappa clover
GBIF description: Note: Many authors have followed Zohary (in Candollea 27: 144. 1972) in treating 930.28 (LINN) as the type. However, this sheet is not annotated in a way to link it to this name, and is indeed the lectotype of another species, T. alpestre L. Although it is possible that Zohary cited sheet 930.28 in error for 930.23 (apparently original material for this name), this cannot be safely assumed, and the name remains at present untypified.
Wikipedia summary: Trifolium lappaceum, the burdock clover, is a species of annual herb in the family Fabaceae. They have a self-supporting growth form and compound, broad leaves.
