115,Trifolium scabrum L.,Trifolium scabrum,Trifolium,Fabaceae,scabrum,L.,,LC,5358977,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Trifolium scabrum,https://www.gbif.org/species/5358977,Rough Clover,"Note: Zohary (in Candollea 27: 137. 1972), followed by several later authors, treated unspecified material in Herb. Clifford (BM) as syntypes. However, the two sheets there associated with this name are not part of a single gathering (so Art. 9.15 does not apply), nor were they explicitly cited by Linnaeus (so they are not syntypes). Lassen's later choice of material in LINN as lectotype is therefore accepted here.",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part T),eng,North America (PRESENT); Albania; Algeria; Azores; Baleares; Belgium; Bulgaria; Canary Is.; Corse; Cyprus; East Aegean Is.; Egypt; France; Germany; Great Britain; Greece; Iran; Iraq; Ireland; Italy,habitat: Terrestrial,Trifolium scabrum,"Trifolium scabrum, the rough clover, is a species of annual herb in the family Fabaceae. They have a self-supporting growth form and compound, broad leaves. Individuals can grow to 0.12 metres.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trifolium_scabrum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Trifolium+scabrum,"Note: Zohary (in Candollea 27: 137. 1972), followed by several later authors, treated unspecified material in Herb. Clifford (BM) as syntypes. However, the two sheets there associated with this name are not part of a single gathering (so Art. 9.15 does not apply), nor were they explicitly cited by Linnaeus (so they are not syntypes). Lassen's later choice of material in LINN as lectotype is therefore accepted here.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 115
