152,Pancratium maritimum L.,Pancratium maritimum,Pancratium,Amaryllidaceae,maritimum,L.,,LC,2853283,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Pancratium maritimum,https://www.gbif.org/species/2853283,Sea Daffodil; Sea-daffodil; Sweet Spider-lily,"Note: The taxonomic identity of the type has provoked differences of opinion, with many authors (e. g. Howard & Staples in J. Arnold Arbor. 64: 513. 1983) treating it as Hymenocallis carolinianum (L.) Herb. but others (e. g. Smith & Garland in Taxon 52: 814. 2003) arguing that it is a depiction of Pancratium maritimum.",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part P),eng,North America (PRESENT); Albania; Algeria; Azores (INTRODUCED); Baleares; Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Bulgaria; Canary Is.; Corse; Cyprus; East Aegean Is.; Egypt; France; Great Britain (INTRODUCED); Greece; Illinois (INTRODUCED); Italy; Kriti; Lebanon-Syria; Libya,habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial,Pancratium maritimum,"Pancratium maritimum, or sea daffodil, is a species of bulbous plant native to both sides of the Mediterranean region and the Black Sea, from the Canary Islands, Portugal, Morocco, and Cyprus, and east to Turkey, Syria, Israel and the Caucasus. Parts of its range on the coasts of the Black Sea include southern Bulgaria, northern Turkey and Georgia. It is also naturalized in southern California, Bermuda and the Azores.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pancratium_maritimum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Pancratium+maritimum,"Note: The taxonomic identity of the type has provoked differences of opinion, with many authors (e. g. Howard & Staples in J. Arnold Arbor. 64: 513. 1983) treating it as Hymenocallis carolinianum (L.) Herb. but others (e. g. Smith & Garland in Taxon 52: 814. 2003) arguing that it is a depiction of Pancratium maritimum.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 152
