lose, 3 - lobed, not globose-inflated; lateral lobes patent, obtuse; middle lobe flat or concave, ovate, wider and longer than the lateral, deeply emarginate or 2 - lobed, sometimes with a tooth in the sinus; speculum reniform or square, shiny, pale blue-violet. Connective obtuse. 2 n = 36.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 187
