191,Cenchrus longispinus (Hack.) Fernald,Cenchrus longispinus,Cenchrus,Poaceae,longispinus,(Hack.) Fernald,,Not assessed,5289731,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Cenchrus longispinus,https://www.gbif.org/species/5289731,"Bohena Beauty; Bohena Beauty, Field Sandbur; Burgrass; Dune Sandbur; Field Sandbur; Gentle Annie; grassburs; Hedgehog Grass; Innocent-weed; Long-spine Sandbur; long-spined sandbur; Longspine Sandbur",cbd_2014_pathway:contaminant,RINSE - Pathways and vectors of biological invasions in Northwest Europe,eng,North America (PRESENT); South America (PRESENT); Alabama; Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northwest (INTRODUCED); Arizona; Arkansas; Bermuda (INTRODUCED); British Columbia; California; Colorado; Connecticut; Costa Rica (INTRODUCED); Delaware; District of Columbia; Dominican Republic (INTRODUCED); Florida; France (INTRODUCED); Georgia; Greece (INTRODUCED),"lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Restinga""]}; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial",Cenchrus longispinus,"Cenchrus longispinus is a species of grass, also known as spiny burr grass or gentle Annie or picco. Its fruits are clumped into ""burrs"" with sharp, barbed spines that can penetrate the hides and mouth of grazing animals. They can also become lodged in human clothing and skin, causing some discomfort. This activity is important for the plant's seed dispersal, as the plant is a summer annual. The species has a prostrate habit when there is no competition for light.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cenchrus_longispinus,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Cenchrus+longispinus,cbd_2014_pathway:contaminant,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 191
