GBIF description: Schefflera actinophylla (Endl.) Harms
Wikipedia summary: Heptapleurum actinophyllum is a tree in the family Araliaceae. It is native to tropical rainforests and gallery forests in northern and northeastern Queensland coasts and the Northern Territory of Australia, as well as New Guinea and Java. Common names include Australian umbrella tree, Queensland umbrella tree, octopus tree and amate.
Distribution: Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh (INTRODUCED); Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Canary Is. (INTRODUCED); Caroline Is. (INTRODUCED); Christmas I. (INTRODUCED); Comoros (INTRODUCED); Dominican Republic (INTRODUCED); Florida (INTRODUCED); Haiti (INTRODUCED); Hawaii (INTRODUCED); Leeward Is. (INTRODUCED); Madeira (INTRODUCED); Marianas (INTRODUCED); Marshall Is. (INTRODUCED); New Guinea; Nicobar Is. (INTRODUCED); Norfolk Is. (INTRODUCED); Northern Territory; Puerto Rico (INTRODUCED)
