193,Cenchrus clandestinus (Hochst. ex Chiov.) Morrone,Cenchrus clandestinus,Cenchrus,Poaceae,clandestinus,(Hochst. ex Chiov.) Morrone,,LC,5828201,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Cenchrus clandestinus,https://www.gbif.org/species/5828201,Kikuyo Grass; Kikuyu grass; Kikuyugrass,"Description. Perennial, mat-forming, stoloniferous. Culms prostrate, 5 - 15 cm high; nodes glabrous; internodes terete or semi-terete, channelled, 1 - 1.5 cm long, 1 - 2.5 mm in diam., glabrous. Leaf sheaths 1.1 - 1.3 cm long, usually distichous, margins hyaline with hairs, hairy or glabrous on both surfaces. Ligules a fringe of hairs, 1 - 2 mm long. Collar glabrous. Leaf blades linear, 1.7 - 7 cm x 2 - 3.5 mm, apex acute, based rounded or obtuse, chartaceous, usually folded, with or without pilose on both surfaces. Inflorescence very short spiciform panicle, ca. 2 x 0.2 - 0.3 cm (including bristles); central axis flattened, 4 - 5 mm long, scabrous; peduncle very short or sessile; 2 - 3 short racemes along central axis; raceme with solitary sessile spikelet subtended by an involucre of bristles. Involucre composed of numerous bristles, slender and filiform, 0.2 - 1.4 cm long, antrorsely scabrous; involucre falling with spikelet; stipe (raceme-based) absent. Spikelets dorsally compressed, lanceolate-linear, 1.6 - 1.8 cm x 1.2 - 1.8 mm, slightly curved. Lower and upper glumes absent. Florets 2. Lower floret sterile. Lower lemma lanceolate-linear, ca. 1.5 cm x 1.2 - 1.8 mm, apex acute, margins folded and membranous, chartaceous, glabrous, 9 - or 11 - nerved. Lower palea absent. Upper floret bisexual, persistent. Upper lemma lanceolate-linear, 1.6 - 1.7 cm x 1.2 - 1.5 mm, apex acute, margins folded and membranous, chartaceous, glabrous, 10 - or 11 - nerved. Upper palea lanceolate-linear, 1.4 - 1.6 cm x 1.2 - 1.5 mm, apex acute, membranous, glabrous, 4 - nerved. Lodicules absent. Stamens 3; filament 3.5 - 5 mm long; anther yellow 2 - 3.5 mm long. Pistil ovary lanceolate, 1.8 - 2 x 0.3 - 0.4 mm; style 2; stigma plumose, 2 - 3 cm long, terminally distinct exserted. Caryopsis not seen.","A taxonomic revision of Cenchrus L. (Poaceae) in Thailand, with lectotypification of Pennisetum macrostachyum Benth.",eng,"No especificado; Chía, vereda Yerbabuena, Sede del Instituto Caro y Cuervo; SFF Iguaque | Parque Nacional Natural Cocuy; Bogotá (INTRODUCED); Africa (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Algeria (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Azores (INTRODUCED); Bolivia (INTRODUCED); Borneo (INTRODUCED); Brazil Southeast (INTRODUCED); Brazil South (INTRODUCED); Burundi; California (INTRODUCED); Cameroon (INTRODUCED); Canary Is. (INTRODUCED); Cape Provinces (INTRODUCED); Chile Central (INTRODUCED); Chile North (INTRODUCED)","lifeForm: grass; lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica"",""Campo de Altitude""]}; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial",Cenchrus clandestinus,"The tropical grass species Cenchrus clandestinus is known by several common names, most often Kikuyu grass. It is native to the highland regions of East Africa that is home to the Kikuyu people. Because of its rapid growth and aggressive nature, it is categorised as a noxious weed in some regions. However, it is also a popular garden lawn species in Australia, New Zealand, South Africa and the southern region of California in the United States, being inexpensive and moderately drought-tolerant. In addition, it is useful as pasture for livestock grazing and serves as a food source for many avian species, including the long-tailed widowbird. The flowering culms are very short and ""hidden"" amongst the leaves, giving this species its specific epithet (clandestinus).",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cenchrus_clandestinus,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Cenchrus+clandestinus,"Description. Perennial, mat-forming, stoloniferous. Culms prostrate, 5 - 15 cm high; nodes glabrous; internodes terete or semi-terete, channelled, 1 - 1.5 cm long, 1 - 2.5 mm in diam., glabrous. Leaf sheaths 1.1 - 1.3 cm long, usually distichous, margins hyaline with hairs, hairy or glabrous on both surfaces. Ligules a fringe of hairs, 1 - 2 mm long. Collar glabrous. Leaf blades linear, 1.7 - 7 cm x 2 - 3.5 mm, apex acute, based rounded or obtuse, chartaceous, usually folded, with or without pilose on both surfaces. Inflorescence very short spiciform panicle, ca. 2 x 0.2 - 0.3 cm (including bristles); central axis flattened, 4 - 5 mm long, scabrous; peduncle very short or sessile; 2 - 3 short racemes along central axis; raceme with solitary sessile spikelet subtended by an involucre of bristles. Involucre composed of numerous bristles, slender and filiform, 0.2 - 1.4 cm long, antrorsely scabrous; involucre falling with spikelet; stipe (raceme-based) absent. Spikelets dorsally compressed, lanceolate-linear, 1.6 - 1.8 cm x 1.2 - 1.8 mm, slightly curved. Lower and upper glumes absent. Florets 2. Lower floret sterile. Lower lemma lanceolate-linear, ca. 1.5 cm x 1.2 - 1.8 mm, apex acute, margins folded and membranous, chartaceous, glabrous, 9 - or 11 - nerved. Lower palea absent. Upper floret bisexual, persistent. Upper lemma lanceolate-linear, 1.6 - 1.7 cm x 1.2 - 1.5 mm, apex acute, margins folded and membranous, chartaceous, glabrous, 10 - or 11 - nerved. Upper palea lanceolate-linear, 1.4 - 1.6 cm x 1.2 - 1.5 mm, apex acute, membranous, glabrous, 4 - nerved. Lodicules absent. Stamens 3; filament 3.5 - 5 mm long; anther yellow 2 - 3.5 mm long. Pistil ovary lanceolate, 1.8 - 2 x 0.3 - 0.4 mm; style 2; stigma plumose, 2 - 3 cm long, terminally distinct exserted. Caryopsis not seen.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 193
