s with or without scabrous along nerve, 1 - or 3 - nerved or nerveless. Lower floret male or sterile. Lower lemma lanceolate, 3 - 6 x 0.8 - 1.3 mm, apex acuminate, chartaceous, glabrous with or without scabrous along nerve, 3 - or 5 - nerved. Lower palea mostly absent or lanceolate, 4.5 - 5.2 x 0.8 - 1 mm, apex acute, margins fold with or without scabrous, membranous, glabrous, 2 - or 3 - nerved. Upper floret bisexual, persistent. Upper lemma lanceolate, 4 - 6.5 x 0.8 - 1.2 mm, apex acuminate, margins with ciliate, coriaceous, glabrous and scabrous near tip, 3 - or 5 - nerved. Upper palea lanceolate, 4.3 - 6.5 x 0.8 - 1.2 mm, apex acuminate, coriaceous, glabrous with or without scabrous near tip, 2 -, 3 - or 5 - nerved. Lodicules absent. Stamens 3, filament 0.3 - 3 mm long, anther yellow, 1.5 - 2.8 mm long. Pistil ovary oblong-lanceolate, 0.6 - 1.5 x 0.1 - 0.5 mm; style 2, 1.5 - 4 mm long; stigma plumose, 2 - 6 mm long. Caryopsis ellipsoid, 1.5 - 2 x 0.8 - 1 mm.","A taxonomic revision of Cenchrus L. (Poaceae) in Thailand, with lectotypification of Pennisetum macrostachyum Benth.",eng,Floridablanca | Los Santos | Rionegro | Tona; Jardín Botánico de Bogotá; Africa (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Aldabra; Algeria; Andaman Is. (INTRODUCED); Angola; Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northwest (INTRODUCED); Assam (INTRODUCED); Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh (INTRODUCED); Belize (INTRODUCED); Benin; Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Bolivia (INTRODUCED); Brazil Northeast (INTRODUCED); Brazil North (INTRODUCED),"lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica"",""Cerrado (lato sensu)"",""Floresta Estacional Semidecidual"",""Floresta Ombrófila Mista""]}; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial",Cenchrus purpureus,"Cenchrus purpureus, synonym Pennisetum purpureum, also known as Napier grass, el