Wikipedia summary: Cenchrus setaceus, commonly known as crimson fountaingrass, is a C4 perennial bunch grass that is native to open, scrubby habitats in East Africa, tropical Africa, the Middle East and south-western Asia. It has been introduced to many parts of the world as an ornamental plant, and has become an invasive species in some of them. It is drought-tolerant, grows fast, reaches 3 feet in height, and has many purple, plumose flower spikes.
Distribution: No especificado; Bogotá (INTRODUCED); Jardín Botánico de Bogotá; Africa (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Afghanistan; Algeria; Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Arizona (INTRODUCED); Baleares (INTRODUCED); Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Bulgaria (INTRODUCED); California (INTRODUCED); Canary Is. (INTRODUCED); Cape Provinces (INTRODUCED); Chad; Colombia (INTRODUCED); Colorado (INTRODUCED); Corse (INTRODUCED); Cyprus (INTRODUCED)
Profile: lifeForm: grass; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial
