204,Smilax aspera L.,Smilax aspera,Smilax,Smilacaceae,aspera,L.,,LC,5295044,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Smilax aspera,https://www.gbif.org/species/5295044,Common Smilax; Rough Bindweed; rough-bindweed,"Note: El-Gadi (in Jafri & El-Gadi, Fl. Libya 57: 77. 1978) indicated 1182.1 (LINN) as type, but this is a Kaehler collection, not received by Linnaeus until 1757 and not, therefore, original material for the name. Cowley (in Polhill, Fl. Trop. E. Africa, Smilacaceae: 2. 1989) indicated Clifford material as the type but did not distinguish between the two sheets preserved there; she made a definitive choice in 1993.",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part S),eng,Africa (PRESENT); Europe & Northern Asia (excluding China) (PRESENT); Southern Asia (PRESENT); Albania; Algeria; Assam; Azores; Baleares; Bangladesh; Canary Is.; China South-Central; Corse; Cyprus; DR Congo; East Aegean Is.; East Himalaya; Eritrea; Ethiopia; France; Greece,habitat: terrestrial,Smilax aspera,"Smilax aspera, with common names common smilax, rough bindweed, sarsaparille, and Mediterranean smilax, is a species of flowering vine in the greenbriar family.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smilax_aspera,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Smilax+aspera,"Note: El-Gadi (in Jafri & El-Gadi, Fl. Libya 57: 77. 1978) indicated 1182.1 (LINN) as type, but this is a Kaehler collection, not received by Linnaeus until 1757 and not, therefore, original material for the name. Cowley (in Polhill, Fl. Trop. E. Africa, Smilacaceae: 2. 1989) indicated Clifford material as the type but did not distinguish between the two sheets preserved there; she made a definitive choice in 1993.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 204
Scientific name: Smilax aspera
