GBIF description: Description. Perennial, tufted, Culms geniculate ascending, 45 - 75 cm high; nodes glabrous; internode subterete, 4 - 13 mm long, 1 - 2 mm in diam., glabrous. Leaf sheaths keeled conspicuous, 4 - 8 cm long, margins hairy, glabrous or hairy. Ligules a fringe of hairs, 1 - 1.5 mm long. Collar glabrous. Leaf blades linear, 16 - 32 cm x 2 - 7 mm, apex acute, base rounded, margins scabrous, chartaceous, both surfaces hairy or lower surface glabrous and upper surface pilose. Inflorescence spiciform panicle, 17 - 33 x 1.5 - 2.2 cm (including bristles); central axis angular, 6 - 11 cm long, axis internode 0.5 - 1.5 mm long, scabrous and puberulose; peduncle terete, 8 - 25 cm long, scabrous; short raceme along central axis; raceme with (1 -) 2 - 3 (- 4) spikelets in cluster, all sessile, subtended by an involucre of bristles. Involucre composed of outer and inner circles; outer circle usually shorter than inner circle; outer involucre of bristles, numerous and filamentous, free, 1 - 7 mm long, antrorsely scabrous; inner involucre of 8 - 13 slightly flattened bristles with 6 - 11 mm long, connate only at the base less than 1 mm long, one conspicuous longest bristle 0.9 - 1.4 cm long, hairy and antrorsely scabrous; involucre falling with spikelets; stipe (raceme-based) ca. 0.5 mm long, hairy. Spikelets dorsally compressed, lanceolate, 3 - 4.4 x 1 - 1.1 mm. Lower glume ovate, 1.7 - 2.4 x 0.8 - 1.2 mm, apex acute, membranous, glabrous, 1 - nerved. Upper glume ovate, 2 - 3 x 1 - 1.3 mm, apex acute, membranous, glabrous, 1 - nerved. Florets 2. Lower floret sterile, rarely male. Lower lemma lanceolate or ovate-lanceolate, 3 - 4 x 1 - 1.5 mm, apex acute or mucronate, membranous, glabrous, 5 or 7 - nerved. Lower palea elliptic or oblong, 2 - 3 x ca. 0.6 mm, apex obtuse or acute, margins folded with antrorsely scabrous, membranous, glabrous, 2 - nerved or palea absent. Upper floret bisexual. Upper lemma lanceolate, 3.2 - 4.3 x 1 - 1.2 mm, apex acute or acuminate, margins hyaline, chartaceous or coriaceous, glabrous, 5 - nerved. Upper palea lanceolate, 3 - 4 x 0.7 - 1.2 mm, apex acuminate, margins hyaline, chartaceous or coriaceous, glabrous 2 - keeled, 2 - nerved. Lodicules absent. Stamens 3; filament ca. 3 mm long; anther yellow 1.5 - 2.5 mm long. Pistil ovary elliptic, 0.4 - 0.8 x 0.2 - 0.5 mm; style 2; stigma plumose. Caryopsis ellipsoid, 1.4 - 1.8 x ca. 1 mm.
Wikipedia summary: Cenchrus ciliaris is a species of grass native to most of Africa, southern Asia, southern Iran, and the extreme south of Europe (Sicily). Other names by which this grass is known include dhaman grass, anjan grass and koluk katai.
