226,Dalbergia melanoxylon Guill. & Perr.,Dalbergia melanoxylon,Dalbergia,Fabaceae,melanoxylon,Guill. & Perr.,,NT,2968897,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Dalbergia melanoxylon,https://www.gbif.org/species/2968897,African blackwood; African Ebony; african-blackwood; African-ebony; Blackwood Dalbergia; Chinese blackwood; Ebony Dalbergia; Grenadille Wood; Mozambique Ebony; Mozambique-ebony; poyi; Rhodesian Bird-Cherry,"Shrub, in open forest, thicket, and grassy savannah; also in cropland, fallow and disturbed sites. C. N.: pau-preto (pt). Uses: firewood, medicinal. Conservation: LC (IUCN 2017) F. Monteiro 1495 (LUAI, LISC)","An annotated checklist of the vascular flora of Quiçama National Park, Angola",eng,Angola; Bangladesh (INTRODUCED); Botswana; Burkina; Cameroon; Caprivi Strip; Central African Republic; Chad; DR Congo; Eritrea; Eswatini; Ethiopia; Guinea; India (INTRODUCED); Ivory Coast; Kenya; Malawi; Mali; Mauritania; Mozambique,"habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Árvore""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}",Dalbergia melanoxylon,"Dalbergia melanoxylon in French Grenadille d'Afrique is a flowering plant in the subfamily Faboideae of the family Fabaceae, native to seasonally dry regions of Africa from Senegal east to Eritrea, to southern regions of Tanzania to Mozambique and south to the north-eastern parts of South Africa. The tree is an important timber species in its native areas; it is used in the manufacture of musical instruments, sculptures vinyago in Swahili language and fine furniture. Populations and genomic resources for genetic biodiversity maintenance in parts of its native range are threatened by overharvesting due to poor or absent conservation planning and by the species' low germination rates.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dalbergia_melanoxylon,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Dalbergia+melanoxylon,"Shrub, in open forest, thicket, and grassy savannah; also in cropland, fallow and disturbed sites. C. N.: pau-preto (pt). Uses: firewood, medicinal. Conservation: LC (IUCN 2017) F. Monteiro 1495 (LUAI, LISC)",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 226
