253,Neltuma alba (Griseb.) C.E.Hughes & G.P.Lewis,Neltuma alba,Neltuma,Fabaceae,alba,(Griseb.) C.E.Hughes & G.P.Lewis,,LR/nt,5358528,EXACT,100,SYNONYM,Prosopis alba,https://www.gbif.org/species/5358528,algarrobo blanco,Voucher: L. Bernardi 18422 (BM).,"Checklist of vascular plants of the Ñeembucú Department, Paraguay",,,,Neltuma alba,"Neltuma alba is a South American tree species that grows in central Argentina, the Gran Chaco ecoregion, and part of the Argentine Mesopotamia, as well as Bolivia, Chile, Paraguay, and Peru. It is known as algarrobo blanco in Spanish. Spanish settlers gave it that name because of its similarity to the European carob tree. Other common names come from Guaraní, including ibopé and igopé.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neltuma_alba,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Neltuma+alba,Voucher: L. Bernardi 18422 (BM).,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 253
