255,Crotalaria spectabilis Roth,Crotalaria spectabilis,Crotalaria,Fabaceae,spectabilis,Roth,,Not assessed,2942727,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Crotalaria spectabilis,https://www.gbif.org/species/2942727,rattle box; rattlebox; showy crotalaria; Showy Rattlebox; showy rattlepod; silent rattlepod,Annual herb,"The checklist of alien seed plants of D.R. Congo, based on evidence from herbarium collections",eng,Introducida en los trópicos de ambos hemisferios (INTRODUCED); Caribbean (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Andaman Is.; Angola (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Arkansas (INTRODUCED); Assam; Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh; Brazil Northeast (INTRODUCED); Brazil North (INTRODUCED); Brazil Southeast (INTRODUCED); Brazil South (INTRODUCED); Brazil West-Central (INTRODUCED); Caroline Is. (INTRODUCED); Central African Republic (INTRODUCED); China South-Central,"lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Arbusto"",""Subarbusto""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial",Crotalaria spectabilis,"Crotalaria spectabilis, the showy rattlebox or showy rattlepod, is a species of flowering plant in the pea family Fabaceae. It is native to the Indian Subcontinent, southern China, and Southeast Asia. It is a perennial herb that grows up to 0.6–1.5 m (24–59 in) tall. It grows in montane grasslands, along forest edges, and within meadows. It was introduced to most of the world's tropics and subtropics and is now a serious agricultural pest species. It is toxic to livestock, causing liver damage.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crotalaria_spectabilis,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Crotalaria+spectabilis,Annual herb,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 255
