IUCN status: LC
Accepted scientific name: Acaciella angustissima
Common names: fern acacia; Prairie Acacia; white-ball acacia
GBIF description: Estados Unidos a Argentina; República Dominicana; introducida en Oceanía
Wikipedia summary: Acaciella angustissima, commonly known as the prairie acacia, white-ball acacia, ocpatl, or palo de pulque, is a species of legume most recognized for its drought tolerance and its ability to be used as a green manure and ground covering. It is a perennial, deciduous, and belongs to the family Fabaceae (beans/legumes) and as it grows it starts as a shrub but eventually matures to a small tree. The tree has a high density of leaves along with small clumps of white flowers and creates 4–7 cm (1.6–2.8 in) long seed pods.
Distribution: Rionegro; SFF Iguaque | Área Natural Única Los Estoraques | Parque Nacional Natural Los Katíos (NATIVE); Jardín Botánico de Bogotá; Argentina Northwest; Arizona; Arkansas; Belize; Bolivia; California; Colombia; Costa Rica; Cuba (INTRODUCED); Ecuador; El Salvador; Florida; Guatemala; Honduras; India (INTRODUCED); Kansas; Louisiana
Profile: habitat: terrestrial; lifeForm: Arbusto, Árbol; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial
Sources: https://www.gbif.org/species/2981071 | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acaciella_angustissima | https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Acaciella+angustissima",ok
269,Gomphocarpus integer (N.E.Br.) Bullock,Gomphocarpus integer,Gomphocarpus,Apocynaceae,integer,(N.E.Br.) Bullock,,Not assessed,3573780,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Gomphocarpus integer,https://www.gbif.org/species/3573780,,,,,Djibouti; Ethiopia; Kenya; Somalia; Tanzania; Ethiopia; Djibouti; Somalia; Kenya; Tanzania,,Gomphocarpus,"Gomphocarpus is a genus of plants in the family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1810. It is in the milkweed subfamily Asclepiadoideae, and its members are considered milkweeds. It is widespread across much of Africa, with a few species naturalized in other regions.Species accepted",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gomphocarpus,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Gomphocarpus+integer,"Gomphocarpus is a genus of plants in the family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1810. It is in the milkweed subfamily Asclepiadoideae, and its members are considered milkweeds. It is widespread across much of Africa, with a few species naturalized in other regions.Species accepted",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 269
Scientific name: Gomphocarpus integer
Full species name: Gomphocarpus integer (N.E.Br.) Bullock
Genus: Gomphocarpus
Family: Apocynaceae
IUCN status: Not assessed
Accepted scientific name: Gomphocarpus integer
Wikipedia summary: Gomphocarpus is a genus of plants in the family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1810. It is in the milkweed subfamily Asclepiadoideae, and its members are considered milkweeds. It is widespread across much of Africa, with a few species naturalized in other regions.Species accepted
Distribution: Djibouti; Ethiopia; Kenya; Somalia; Tanzania; Ethiopia; Djibouti; Somalia; Kenya; Tanzania
