275,Mussaenda frondosa L.,Mussaenda frondosa,Mussaenda,Rubiaceae,frondosa,L.,,LC,2892470,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Mussaenda frondosa,https://www.gbif.org/species/2892470,Bangkok rose; wild mussaenda,"Note: Although originally appearing as "" M. fr. [fructu] frondoso "", the name is to be cited as "" M. frondosa "" (Art. 23.7, Ex. 18). Smith (in J. Arnold Arbor. 26: 104. 1945) stated that "" the actual type is a collection of Hermann from Ceylon "" but did not indicate where this might be held (BM, L, etc.). Jayaweera's explicit statement is therefore accepted here as typifying the name.",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part M),eng,Andaman Is.; Assam; Bangladesh; Borneo; Cambodia; Caroline Is.; China Southeast (INTRODUCED); East Himalaya; Hainan (INTRODUCED); India; Jawa; Lesser Sunda Is.; Malaya; Maluku; Nepal; New Guinea; Nicobar Is.; Queensland (INTRODUCED); Sri Lanka; Sulawesi,"habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Arbusto""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}",Mussaenda frondosa,"Mussaenda frondosa, commonly known as the wild mussaenda or dhobi tree, is a plant of family Rubiaceae. It is a shrub that grows to about 1.5–2 m tall. Like most other Mussaenda species, they have a bract beneath their flowers, which in this species is white in colour.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mussaenda_frondosa,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Mussaenda+frondosa,"Note: Although originally appearing as "" M. fr. [fructu] frondoso "", the name is to be cited as "" M. frondosa "" (Art. 23.7, Ex. 18). Smith (in J. Arnold Arbor. 26: 104. 1945) stated that "" the actual type is a collection of Hermann from Ceylon "" but did not indicate where this might be held (BM, L, etc.). Jayaweera's explicit statement is therefore accepted here as typifying the name.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 275
Scientific name: Mussaenda frondosa
Full species name: Mussaenda frondosa L.
Genus: Mussaenda
