282,Gynura aurantiaca (Blume) DC.,Gynura aurantiaca,Gynura,Asteraceae,aurantiaca,(Blume) DC.,,Not assessed,3115470,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Gynura aurantiaca,https://www.gbif.org/species/3115470,Purple velvet plant; purple velvetplant; purple-passionvine; royal velvetplant; Velvet Plant; Velvetplant,Annual herb,"The checklist of alien seed plants of D.R. Congo, based on evidence from herbarium collections",eng,North America (PRESENT); Colombia (INTRODUCED); Costa Rica (INTRODUCED); DR Congo (INTRODUCED); El Salvador (INTRODUCED); Florida (INTRODUCED); Guatemala (INTRODUCED); Honduras (INTRODUCED); India (INTRODUCED); Jawa; Leeward Is. (INTRODUCED); Nicobar Is. (INTRODUCED); Philippines (INTRODUCED); Sulawesi; Sumatera; Trinidad-Tobago (INTRODUCED); Vietnam (INTRODUCED); Northern America (PRESENT); Malesia (PRESENT); Southern South America (INTRODUCED),"habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; lifeForm: Hierba; lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}",Gynura aurantiaca,"Gynura aurantiaca, called purple passion or velvet plant, is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family Asteraceae. It is native to Southeast Asia but grown in many other places as a house plant. In warm regions, it is frequently grown outdoors on patios and in gardens rather than inside buildings, and hence it has escaped into the wild in Africa, Australia, South America, Mesoamerica, Florida, and a few other places.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gynura_aurantiaca,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Gynura+aurantiaca,Annual herb,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 282
