Wikipedia summary: Schkuhria pinnata, the canchalagua or dwarf Mexican marigold, is a small, dainty, pioneer annual herb of the family Asteraceae and widespread in the tropics. It is regarded as a naturalised weed with low ecological impact.
Distribution: East Africa (PRESENT); Bolivia (PRESENT); Brazilia Distrito Federal (PRESENT); São Paulo (PRESENT); Belgium [I]; Germany [I]; Spain [I]; France [I]; Romania [I]; Ethiopia [I]; Eritrea [I]; Zimbabwe [I]; Mozambique [I]; Namibia [I]; Botswana [I]; South Africa [I] (widespread); Lesotho [I]; Eswatini [Swaziland] [I]; St. Helena [I]; Australia [I] (Queensland [I], New South Wales [I], Victoria [I]); USA (Arizona, New Mexico, Texas); Mexico (Aguascalientes, Chiapas, Chihuahua, Coahuila, Colima, Ciudad de Mexico, Durango, Guanajuato, Guerrero, Hidalgo, Jalisco, México State, Michoacán, Morelos, Nayarit, Nuevo Leon, Oaxaca, Puebla, Queretaro, San Luis Potosi, Sinaloa, Sonora, Tamaulipas, Tlaxcala, Veracruz, Zacatecas); Guatemala; El Salvador; Honduras; Nicaragua; Costa Rica; Colombia (Cundinamarca, Nariño); Venezuela (Merida); Ecuador; Peru; Bolivia (Chuquisaca, Cochabamba, La Paz, Santa Cruz); WC-Brazil (Brazília Distrito Federal); SE-Brazil (São Paulo); Paraguay (Amambay, Central); Uruguay (Colonia, Lavalleja, Paysandu, Rio Negro, Salto, San Jose, Soriano, Tacuarembo); Argentina (Buenos Aires, Catamarca, Chaco, Cordoba, Entre Rios, Jujuy, La Pampa, La Rioja, Mendoza, Neuquén, Rio Negro, Salta, Santiago del Estero, Santa Fe, San Juan, San Luis, Tucuman); Chile (Arica y Parinacota, Tarapacá, Coquimbo); Belgium (PRESENT); Flemish Region (PRESENT); Walloon Region (PRESENT); BR (PRESENT); BR (NATURALISED); CZ (PRESENT); Czech Republic (DOUBTFUL); DK (PRESENT); DK; Spain (DOUBTFUL); France (DOUBTFUL); FR (PRESENT); FR; Channel Is. (DOUBTFUL); Great Britain (DOUBTFUL)
