307,Aristea ecklonii Baker,Aristea ecklonii,Aristea,Iridaceae,ecklonii,Baker,,Not assessed,2744906,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Aristea ecklonii,https://www.gbif.org/species/2744906,Blue Corn-Lily; blue stars; Star Capeblue,Africa,DAISIE - Inventory of alien invasive species in Europe,,Burundi; California (INTRODUCED); Cameroon; Cape Provinces; DR Congo; Eswatini; France (INTRODUCED); Great Britain (INTRODUCED); India (INTRODUCED); Jamaica (INTRODUCED); KwaZulu-Natal; Mozambique; New South Wales (INTRODUCED); New Zealand North (INTRODUCED); New Zealand South (INTRODUCED); Northern Provinces; Queensland (INTRODUCED); Rwanda; Sri Lanka (INTRODUCED); Tanzania,habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial,Aristea ecklonii,"Aristea ecklonii is a plant species in the Iridaceae, first described in 1866. It is native to central and southern Africa from South Africa north to Cameroon and Tanzania. The plant is an evergreen perennial with small, blue flowers, growing in clumps with upright, grass-like leaves 15–18 in (38–46 cm) in height.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aristea_ecklonii,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Aristea+ecklonii,Africa,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 307
