316,Couroupita guianensis Aubl.,Couroupita guianensis,Couroupita,Lecythidaceae,guianensis,Aubl.,,LC,3082562,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Couroupita guianensis,https://www.gbif.org/species/3082562,Cannonball Tree; cannonball-tree,Especie de planta arbórea nativa con categoría de amenaza LC (preocupación menor - UICN 2018). Se encuentra entre los 200 - 560 metros de altitud. Es usada comúnmente en procesos de restauración ecológica como alimento y hábitat de fauna silvestre.,Lista anotada de las especies forestales sembradas en el programa de restauración ecológica participativa ReverdeC,,Departamentos del Caquetá y Guaviare: Parque Nacional Natural Serranía de Chiribiquete; Cimitarra; Zona oriental; Reserva Nacional Natural Puinawai | ReservaNacional Natural Nukak | Parque Nacional Natural Sierra de la Macarena | Parque Nacional Natural Tinigua (NATIVE); Jardín Botánico de Bogotá; Caribbean (PRESENT); Middle America (PRESENT); South America (PRESENT); Andaman Is. (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh (INTRODUCED); Bolivia; Brazil North; Brazil Southeast (INTRODUCED); Colombia; Costa Rica (INTRODUCED); Cuba (INTRODUCED); Dominican Republic (INTRODUCED); Ecuador; Florida (INTRODUCED); French Guiana,"lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Árvore""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Floresta de Terra Firme""]}; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; lifeForm: Árbol; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial",Couroupita guianensis,"Couroupita guianensis, known by a variety of common names including cannonball tree, is a deciduous tree in the flowering plant family Lecythidaceae. It is native to lowland tropical rainforests of Central and South America, from Costa Rica, south to Brazil and northern Bolivia and it is cultivated in many other tropical areas throughout the world because of its fragrant flowers and large fruit, which are brownish grey. There are potential medicinal uses for many parts of Couroupita guianensis, and the tree has cultural and religious significance in South and Southeast Asia. In Sri Lanka and India, the cannonball tree has been widely misidentified as the Sal tree, after its introduction to the island by the British in 1881, and has been included as a common item in Buddhist temples as a result.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Couroupita_guianensis,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Couroupita+guianensis,Especie de planta arbórea nativa con categoría de amenaza LC (preocupación menor - UICN 2018). Se encuentra entre los 200 - 560 metros de altitud. Es usada comúnmente en procesos de restauración ecológica como alimento y hábitat de fauna silvestre.,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 316
Scientific name: Couroupita guianensis
Full species name: Couroupita guianensis Aubl.
Genus: Couroupita
Family: Lecythidaceae
IUCN status: LC
