r - lanceolate; inner perianth-segments 6 - 7 mm, oblong-, tri­ angular- or linear-lanceolate, more intensely coloured than the outer, glabrous, papillose or densely hairy. Labellum 8 - 10 mm, suborbicular, obovate or somewhat square, subentire, rarely indistinctly 3 - lobed, velutinous, with broadly conical, short, inconspicuous basal protuberances, sometimes with a narrow, yellow, glabrous marginal zone, usually with a small appendage; speculum annular or square, usually H-shaped, blue or dark purplish, with whitish or yellow margin. Connective acute. 2 / 2 = 36, 38.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 343
