367,Cymbalaria aequitriloba (Viv.) A.Chev.,Cymbalaria aequitriloba,Cymbalaria,Plantaginaceae,aequitriloba,(Viv.) A.Chev.,,Not assessed,7331882,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Cymbalaria aequitriloba,https://www.gbif.org/species/7331882,,,,,Baleares; Corse; Italy; Sardegna; Baleares; Corsica; Sardinia; Italy (incl. Giglio Isl.); FR; PT (PRESENT); SE (ABSENT),habitat: Terrestrial,Pennywort,"Pennywort is a common name given to several different plants around the world. In general they have round leaves and a low-growing habit. Pennywort may refer to:In Asia: the edible Asiatic pennywort, Centella asiatica, also known as centella, Indian pennywort, or gotukola. In Europe: Navelwort, Umbilicus rupestris, known as penny-pies, wall pennywort, or kidneywort, a succulent, perennial flowering plant in the stonecrop family Crassulaceae. Water pennywort, the genus Hydrocotyle, known as floating pennywort, Indian pennywort, marsh penny, thick-leaved pennywort, or even white rot, aquatic or semi-aquatic plants such as the edible dollarweed, Hydrocotyle umbellata. Liver leaf, Anemone hepatica, also known as liverwort. Virginian pennywort, Obolaria virginica. Cymbalaria muralis. Cymbalaria aequitriloba, tiny ivy-like leaves with copious purple-pink flowers with yellow throats.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pennywort,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Cymbalaria+aequitriloba,"Pennywort is a common name given to several different plants around the world. In general they have round leaves and a low-growing habit. Pennywort may refer to:In Asia: the edible Asiatic pennywort, Centella asiatica, also known as centella, Indian pennywort, or gotukola. In Europe: Navelwort, Umbilicus rupestris, known as penny-pies, wall pennywort, or kidneywort, a succulent, perennial flowering plant in the stonecrop family Crassulaceae. Water pennywort, the genus Hydrocotyle, known as floating pennywort, Indian pennywort, marsh penny, thick-leaved pennywort, or even white rot, aquatic or semi-aquatic plants such as the edible dollarweed, Hydrocotyle umbellata. Liver leaf, Anemone hepatica, also known as liverwort. Virginian pennywort, Obolaria virginica. Cymbalaria muralis. Cymbalaria aequitriloba, tiny ivy-like leaves with copious purple-pink flowers with yellow throats.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 367
Scientific name: Cymbalaria aequitriloba
Full species name: Cymbalaria aequitriloba (Viv.) A.Chev.
Genus: Cymbalaria
Family: Plantaginaceae
IUCN status: Not assessed
Accepted scientific name: Cymbalaria aequitriloba
Wikipedia summary: Pennywort is a common name given to several different plants around the world. In general they have round leaves and a low-growing habit. Pennywort may refer to:In Asia: the edible Asiatic pennywort, Centella asiatica, also known as centella, Indian pennywort, or gotukola. In Europe: Navelwort, Umbilicus rupestris, known as penny-pies, wall pennywort, or kidneywort, a succulent, perennial flowering plant in the stonecrop family Crassulaceae. Water pennywort, the genus Hydrocotyle, known as floating pennywort, Indian pennywort, marsh penny, thick-leaved pennywort, or even white rot, aquatic or semi-aquatic plants such as the edible dollarweed, Hydrocotyle umbellata. Liver leaf, Anemone hepatica, also known as liverwort. Virginian pennywort, Obolaria virginica. Cymbalaria muralis. Cymbalaria aequitriloba, tiny ivy-like leaves with copious purple-pink flowers with yellow throats.
Distribution: Baleares; Corse; Italy; Sardegna; Baleares; Corsica; Sardinia; Italy (incl. Giglio Isl.); FR; PT (PRESENT); SE (ABSENT)
