379,Dryopteris dilatata (Hoffm.) A.Gray,Dryopteris dilatata,Dryopteris,Dryopteridaceae,dilatata,(Hoffm.) A.Gray,,LC,5275103,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Dryopteris dilatata,https://www.gbif.org/species/5275103,Broad Buckler Fern; Broad Buckler-Fern; Broad Wood Fern; Common Buckler-Fern; Mountain Wood Fern,terrestrial,"Validated red lists of Flanders, Belgium",eng,Albania; Altay; Argentina South (INTRODUCED); Austria; Azores; Baltic States; Belarus; Belgium; Bulgaria; Central European Russia; Corse; Czechia-Slovakia; Denmark; Falkland Is. (INTRODUCED); Finland; France; Føroyar; Germany; Great Britain; Greece,habitat: Terrestrial,Dryopteris dilatata,"Dryopteris dilatata, the broad buckler-fern, is a robust species of deciduous or semievergreen fern in the family Dryopteridaceae, native to Europe, particularly western and central Europe. In southern Europe, it is mostly found in mountainous regions. It is also found between the Black Sea and the Caspian Sea. It grows to 90 cm (35 in) tall by 120 cm (47 in) wide, with dark green tripinnate fronds, the ribs covered in brown scales.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dryopteris_dilatata,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Dryopteris+dilatata,terrestrial,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 379
