380,Dryopteris expansa (C.Presl) Fraser-Jenk. & Jermy,Dryopteris expansa,Dryopteris,Dryopteridaceae,expansa,(C.Presl) Fraser-Jenk. & Jermy,,LC,5275102,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Dryopteris expansa,https://www.gbif.org/species/5275102,Alpine Buckler Fern; Broad Buckler Fern; broad spinulose shield fern; Northern Buckler Fern; Northern Buckler-Fern; Northern Wood Fern; spiny wood fern; Spread Wood Fern; Spreading Wood Fern; Spreading Woodfern,medicinal and aromatic,Nordic Crop Wild Relative (CWR) Checklist,,North America (PRESENT); Alaska; Albania; Alberta; Altay; Amur; Austria; Baltic States; Belarus; Belgium; British Columbia; Bulgaria; Buryatiya; California; Central European Russia; China North-Central; Chita; Colorado; Corse; Czechia-Slovakia,,Dryopteris expansa,"Dryopteris expansa, the alpine buckler fern, northern buckler-fern or spreading wood fern, is a species of perennial fern native to cool temperate and subarctic regions of the Northern Hemisphere, south at high altitudes in mountains to Spain and Greece in southern Europe, to Japan in eastern Asia, and to central California in North America. It prefers cool, moist mixed or evergreen forests and rock crevices on alpine slopes, often growing on rotting logs and tree stumps and rocky slopes. It is characteristically riparian in nature, and is especially associated with stream banks.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dryopteris_expansa,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Dryopteris+expansa,medicinal and aromatic,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 380
