382,Empetrum nigrum L.,Empetrum nigrum,Empetrum,Ericaceae,nigrum,L.,,Not assessed,8925249,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Empetrum nigrum,https://www.gbif.org/species/8925249,Black Crowberry; Blackberry; Crakeberry; Crowberry; Crowberry agg.; Curlew-berry; curlewberry; heathberry,"Lectotype (Good in J. Linn. Soc., Bot. 47: 512. 1927): Herb. Linn. No. 1160.2 (LINN).",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part E),eng,"Innherred, and especially in Inderøy; In Norway and Iceland; North America (PRESENT); Alaska; Albania; Alberta; Aleutian Is.; Altay; Amur; Austria; Baltic States (DOUBTFUL); Belarus; Belgium; British Columbia; Bulgaria; Buryatiya; California; Central European Russia; China North-Central; Chita",,Empetrum nigrum,"Empetrum nigrum, the crowberry, black crowberry, mossberry, rockberry, or, in western Alaska, Labrador, etc., blackberry, is a flowering plant species in the heather family Ericaceae with a near circumboreal distribution in the Northern Hemisphere. The scientific name of the plant comes from the combination of the Greek for 'upon a rock' and the Latin for black. North American Indigenous names for this species include asiavik (Iñupiaq), dineechʼúh (Gwichʼin), paurngaq (Inuktut), xéelʼi (Tlingít), xa skáawaa (Haida), and ts'nełt'ida (Dena’ina).",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empetrum_nigrum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Empetrum+nigrum,"Lectotype (Good in J. Linn. Soc., Bot. 47: 512. 1927): Herb. Linn. No. 1160.2 (LINN).",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 382
