383,Epipactis atrorubens (Hoffm.) Besser,Epipactis atrorubens,Epipactis,Orchidaceae,atrorubens,(Hoffm.) Besser,,LC,5318958,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Epipactis atrorubens,https://www.gbif.org/species/5318958,Dark Red Helleborine; Dark-Red Helleborine; Royal Helleborine,"Rhizome short, more or less horizontal. Stem (15 -) 20 - 60 (- 100) cm, glabrous or sparsely pubescent, violet below, with sheathing scales. Leaves distichous, 5 - 10, 4 - 10 x 1 - 5 - 4 - 5 cm, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, acute to acuminate. Raceme 7 - 25 cm, 8 - to 18 - flowered, the rhachis densely pubescent; bracts lanceolate, acute, the lowest equalling or sometimes exceeding flowers. Flowers patent; perianth-segments deep purple, the outer 6 - 7 mm, ovate, acuminate, the inner elliptical. Labellum 5 * 5 - 6 * 5 mm; hypochile cupuliform, green, with red margin, with red spots inside; epichile cordate-reniform, acute, with recurved apex, wider than long, deep reddish-purple, with 2 (- 3) rugose protuberances at base. Rostellum persistent. Ovary densely pubescent. 2 n = 40 + 0 - 7 B.",CCIII Orchidaceae,eng,North America (PRESENT); Albania; Austria; Baltic States; Belarus; Belgium; Bulgaria; Central European Russia; Czechia-Slovakia; Denmark; East European Russia; Finland; France; Germany; Great Britain; Greece; Hungary; Ireland; Italy; Kazakhstan,,Epipactis atrorubens,"Epipactis atrorubens, the dark-red helleborine or royal helleborine, is an herbaceous plant in the orchid family, Orchidaceae.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epipactis_atrorubens,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Epipactis+atrorubens,"Rhizome short, more or less horizontal. Stem (15 -) 20 - 60 (- 100) cm, glabrous or sparsely pubescent, violet below, with sheathing scales. Leaves distichous, 5 - 10, 4 - 10 x 1 - 5 - 4 - 5 cm, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, acute to acuminate. Raceme 7 - 25 cm, 8 - to 18 - flowered, the rhachis densely pubescent; bracts lanceolate, acute, the lowest equalling or sometimes exceeding flowers. Flowers patent; perianth-segments deep purple, the outer 6 - 7 mm, ovate, acuminate, the inner elliptical. Labellum 5 * 5 - 6 * 5 mm; hypochile cupuliform, green, with red margin, with red spots inside; epichile cordate-reniform, acute, with recurved apex, wider than long, deep reddish-purple, with 2 (- 3) rugose protuberances at base. Rostellum persistent. Ovary densely pubescent. 2 n = 40 + 0 - 7 B.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 383
Scientific name: Epipactis atrorubens
Full species name: Epipactis atrorubens (Hoffm.) Besser
Genus: Epipactis
Family: Orchidaceae
IUCN status: LC
Accepted scientific name: Epipactis atrorubens
Common names: Dark Red Helleborine; Dark-Red Helleborine; Royal Helleborine
GBIF description: Rhizome short, more or less horizontal. Stem (15 -) 20 - 60 (- 100) cm, glabrous or sparsely pubescent, violet below, with sheathing scales. Leaves distichous, 5 - 10, 4 - 10 x 1 - 5 - 4 - 5 cm, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, acute to acuminate. Raceme 7 - 25 cm, 8 - to 18 - flowered, the rhachis densely pubescent; bracts lanceolate, acute, the lowest equalling or sometimes exceeding flowers. Flowers patent; perianth-segments deep purple, the outer 6 - 7 mm, ovate, acuminate, the inner elliptical. Labellum 5 * 5 - 6 * 5 mm; hypochile cupuliform, green, with red margin, with red spots inside; epichile cordate-reniform, acute, with recurved apex, wider than long, deep reddish-purple, with 2 (- 3) rugose protuberances at base. Rostellum persistent. Ovary densely pubescent. 2 n = 40 + 0 - 7 B.
Wikipedia summary: Epipactis atrorubens, the dark-red helleborine or royal helleborine, is an herbaceous plant in the orchid family, Orchidaceae.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Albania; Austria; Baltic States; Belarus; Belgium; Bulgaria; Central European Russia; Czechia-Slovakia; Denmark; East European Russia; Finland; France; Germany; Great Britain; Greece; Hungary; Ireland; Italy; Kazakhstan
