385,Epipactis microphylla (Ehrh.) Sw.,Epipactis microphylla,Epipactis,Orchidaceae,microphylla,(Ehrh.) Sw.,,NT,5318948,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Epipactis microphylla,https://www.gbif.org/species/5318948,,,,,Albania; Algeria; Austria; Baleares; Belgium; Bulgaria; Corse; Cyprus; Czechia-Slovakia; East Aegean Is. (DOUBTFUL); France; Germany; Greece; Hungary; Iran; Italy; Kriti; Krym; NW. Balkan Pen.; North Caucasus,,Epipactis microphylla,"Epipactis microphylla, the small-leaved helleborine, is a species of orchid. It is native to much of Europe and to Southwest Asia as far east as Iran though noticeably absent from the British Isles and from Scandinavia. It has also been found in North Africa, in the Babor mountains in Little Kabylia, Algeria.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epipactis_microphylla,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Epipactis+microphylla,"Epipactis microphylla, the small-leaved helleborine, is a species of orchid. It is native to much of Europe and to Southwest Asia as far east as Iran though noticeably absent from the British Isles and from Scandinavia. It has also been found in North Africa, in the Babor mountains in Little Kabylia, Algeria.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 385
