389,Epipactis purpurata Sm.,Epipactis purpurata,Epipactis,Orchidaceae,purpurata,Sm.,,LC,5318906,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Epipactis purpurata,https://www.gbif.org/species/5318906,Violet Helleborine,". Rhizome short, vertical. Stem 20 - 70 cm, pubescent above, purplish below, with sheathing scales. Leaves spirally arranged, 5 - 10, 6 - 10 x 2 - 5 cm, ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate, acute to shortly acuminate, greyish or purplish. Raceme 15 - 25 cm, many-flowered; bracts linear, acuminate, the lower usually exceeding flowers. Flowers obliquely pendent when mature; outer perianth-segments 10 - 12 mm, lanceolate, subobtuse, green outside, whitish inside, the inner whitish, sometimes with pinkish tinge. Labellum 8 - 10 mm; hypochile cupuliform, greenish outside, usually mottled with violet inside; epichile triangular-cordate, acute, with recurved apex, as long as or longer than wide, whitish, with 2 - 3 smooth, confluent basal protuberances. Rostellum persistent. Ovary scabridulous. In = 40.",CCIII Orchidaceae,eng,Austria; Baltic States; Belgium; Bulgaria; Czechia-Slovakia; Denmark; France; Germany; Great Britain; Greece; Hungary; Iran; Italy; NW. Balkan Pen.; Poland; Romania; Spain; Switzerland; Transcaucasus; Ukraine,,Epipactis purpurata,"Epipactis purpurata, the violet helleborine, is an orchid widely distributed in Europe.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epipactis_purpurata,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Epipactis+purpurata,". Rhizome short, vertical. Stem 20 - 70 cm, pubescent above, purplish below, with sheathing scales. Leaves spirally arranged, 5 - 10, 6 - 10 x 2 - 5 cm, ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate, acute to shortly acuminate, greyish or purplish. Raceme 15 - 25 cm, many-flowered; bracts linear, acuminate, the lower usually exceeding flowers. Flowers obliquely pendent when mature; outer perianth-segments 10 - 12 mm, lanceolate, subobtuse, green outside, whitish inside, the inner whitish, sometimes with pinkish tinge. Labellum 8 - 10 mm; hypochile cupuliform, greenish outside, usually mottled with violet inside; epichile triangular-cordate, acute, with recurved apex, as long as or longer than wide, whitish, with 2 - 3 smooth, confluent basal protuberances. Rostellum persistent. Ovary scabridulous. In = 40.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 389
