Wikipedia summary: Erucastrum gallicum is an annual or biennial plant in the family Brassicaceae known by the common names hairy rocket and common dogmustard. It is a low growing plant with an erect upright habit or sometimes with ascending tops with bright yellow flowers. Plants bloom in late spring through the summer into early autumn. As plants bloom the stems extend upward and when finished blooming plants are 30 to 60 centimeters long. The plant is native to Eurasia but is an introduced species in many areas of the world, including much of North America.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Alabama (INTRODUCED); Albania; Alberta (INTRODUCED); Austria; Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Baltic States (INTRODUCED); Belarus (INTRODUCED); Belgium (INTRODUCED); British Columbia (INTRODUCED); California (INTRODUCED); Central European Russia (INTRODUCED); Connecticut (INTRODUCED); Czechia-Slovakia (INTRODUCED); Denmark (INTRODUCED); East European Russia (INTRODUCED); Ecuador (INTRODUCED); Florida (INTRODUCED); France; Germany
