407,Hypericum coris L.,Hypericum coris,Hypericum,Hypericaceae,coris,L.,,Not assessed,3713724,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Hypericum coris,https://www.gbif.org/species/3713724,,"Lectotype (designated here by Robson): [icon] "" Coris lutea, C. B. P. legitima "" in Morison, Pl. Hist. Univ. 2: 469, s. 5, t. 6, f. 4. 1680. - Epitype (designated here by Robson): France. Alpes Maritimes entre Ste Agnes et la Sommet de Col de la Madone de Gorbio, 12 Jul 1972, Van Assche s. n. (BM; iso- BR).",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part H),eng,France; Great Britain (INTRODUCED); Italy; Switzerland; Switzerland; SE-France; N- & C-Italy; CH; FR; NO,,Hypericum coris,"Hypericum coris, the heath-leaved St. John's wort, also called yellow coris, is a species of flowering plant in the family Hypericaceae, and is the type species of sect. Coridium. It is a low shrub, and it is found in Switzerland and northwestern Italy. The species has been a popular garden plant since the 18th century, valued for its long flowering period and for how well it adapts to cultivation.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypericum_coris,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Hypericum+coris,"Lectotype (designated here by Robson): [icon] "" Coris lutea, C. B. P. legitima "" in Morison, Pl. Hist. Univ. 2: 469, s. 5, t. 6, f. 4. 1680. - Epitype (designated here by Robson): France. Alpes Maritimes entre Ste Agnes et la Sommet de Col de la Madone de Gorbio, 12 Jul 1972, Van Assche s. n. (BM; iso- BR).",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 407
