Wikipedia summary: Anemonoides is a genus of flowering plants in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae. Plants of the genus are native to the temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere, on the continents of North America, Europe, and Asia. The generic name Anemonoides means ""anemone-like"", a reminder that many of the species were formerly included within the plant genus Anemone.
