Wikipedia summary: Pelargonium inquinans, the scarlet geranium, is a species of plant in the genus Pelargonium. It is a shrub endemic to South Africa, ranging from Mpumalanga to KwaZulu-Natal and Eastern Cape provinces. It is one of the ancestors of the hybrid line of horticultural pelargoniums, referred to as the zonal group. They can easily be propagated by seeds and cuttings.
