Wikipedia summary: Angelica is a genus of about 90 species of tall biennial and perennial herbs in the family Apiaceae, native to temperate and subarctic regions of the Northern Hemisphere, reaching as far north as Iceland, Sápmi, and Greenland. They grow to 1–3 m tall, with large bipinnate leaves and large compound umbels of white or greenish-white flowers. It shows variations in fruit anatomy, leaf morphology, and subterranean structures. The genes are extremely polymorphic.
Distribution: Global (PRESENT); FR
Sources: https://www.gbif.org/species/5928331 | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angelica | https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Angelica+heterocarpa",ok
