Wikipedia summary: Silene suecica is a species of plant in the family Caryophyllaceae. Its common name is red Alpine catchfly and its natural habitat is the mountains of Norway and Sweden but it is sometimes found near the coasts and it is also found in the Alps and the Pyrenees, Greenland and North America.
Distribution: Austria; East European Russia; Finland; France; Great Britain; Greenland; Iceland; Italy; Labrador; Newfoundland; North European Russia; Northwest European Russia; Norway; Nunavut; Québec; Spain; Sweden; Switzerland; Iceland; England (NW-England: Cumberland, C-Scotland: Meikle Kilrannock); Norway; Sweden; Finland; Switzerland; Austria; Spain; Andorra; France; Italy; European Russia; Greenland; Canada (Newfoundland, Labrador, Nunavut, Quebec); Labrador (PRESENT)
