Wikipedia summary: Eriocapitella hupehensis, a species of flowering plant in the Ranunculaceae family of plants and has an extensive native distribution across a large area of Asia. The plant was previously known as Anemone hupehensis and is often still referred to as such. Together with several closely related species and hybrids between these species, in horticulture these plants are often referred to as Japanese anemones.
Distribution: Oceania (PRESENT); Southern Asia (PRESENT); Assam; China North-Central; China South-Central; China Southeast; Czechia-Slovakia (INTRODUCED); Denmark (INTRODUCED); East Himalaya; Ecuador (INTRODUCED); Germany (INTRODUCED); Korea (INTRODUCED); Myanmar; Nepal; Sweden (INTRODUCED); Taiwan; Germany [I]; China (N-Guangdong, N-Guangxi, Guizhou, W-Hubei, Jiangxi, S-Shaanxi, Sichuan, Yunnan, E-Zhejiang); North Korea [c]; South Korea [c]; Taiwan; Myanmar (Kachin, Sagaing); BR (MANAGED); NO
