530,Thesium pyrenaicum Pourr.,Thesium pyrenaicum,Thesium,Thesiaceae,pyrenaicum,Pourr.,,Not assessed,5579175,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Thesium pyrenaicum,https://www.gbif.org/species/5579175,Meadow Bastard Toadflax,"DLN 5195, Spain, P. Escobar & al. 492 / 04 (MA), OP 184321, OP 172402, OP 172108; DLN 5196, Spain, M. A. García & al. MAG- 3915 (MA), OP 184322, OP 172403, OP 172109;","A tough nutlet to crack: Resolving the phylogeny of Thesium (Thesiaceae), the largest genus in Santalales",eng,Austria; Belgium; Czechia-Slovakia; France; Germany; Italy; NW. Balkan Pen.; Netherlands; Poland; Portugal; Spain; Switzerland; Belgium (PRESENT); Walloon Region (PRESENT); CH; DE; FR; Grand Duchy of Luxembourg (PRESENT),,Thesium pyrenaicum,"Thesium pyrenaicum is a species in the genus Thesium of the sandalwood family, Santalaceae. The genera and species of this family are usually semiparasites feeding on other plants. T. pyrenaicum or meadowflax is a perennial herb between 15 and 50 cm high. It occurs in Western Europe. With standing stem(s) the leaves are lineal, with three veins, alternate, without stipules. The flowers, with 3-5 petals, are tube-shaped, and bloom in June and July. The petal tops roll in during the fruiting season. It has 5-9 stamen with distinct ovaries. The seeds are nutlike. The fruit is shorter than the flower.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thesium_pyrenaicum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Thesium+pyrenaicum,"DLN 5195, Spain, P. Escobar & al. 492 / 04 (MA), OP 184321, OP 172402, OP 172108; DLN 5196, Spain, M. A. García & al. MAG- 3915 (MA), OP 184322, OP 172403, OP 172109;",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 530
