Wikipedia summary: Angelica atropurpurea, known commonly as purplestem angelica, great angelica, American angelica, high angelica, and masterwort, is a species of flowering plant that can be found in moist and swampy woodlands, mostly by riverbanks, in eastern North America.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Connecticut; Delaware; Illinois; Indiana; Iowa; Kentucky; Labrador; Maine; Maryland; Massachusetts; Michigan; Minnesota; New Brunswick; New Hampshire; New Jersey; New York; Newfoundland; North Carolina; Nova Scotia
