577,Adonis vernalis L.,Adonis vernalis,Adonis,Ranunculaceae,vernalis,L.,,LC,5371711,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Adonis vernalis,https://www.gbif.org/species/5371711,False Hellebore; oxeye; pheasant's-eye; Spring Adonis; Spring Pheasant's Eye; Yellow Adonis; Yellow Pheasant's Eye; yellow pheasants-eye,"2. Adonis flore dodecapetalo, fructu ovato. Adonis radice perenni. Hort. cliff. 231. Fl. suec. 456. It. oel. 73. Roy. lugdb. 488. Sauv. monsp. 253. Helleborus niger tenuifolius, buphthalmi flore. Bauh. pin. 186. Buphthalmum. Dod. pempt. 261.","Species plantarum: exhibentes plantas rite cognitas, ad genera relatas, cum differentiis specificis, nominibus trivialibus, synonymis selectis, locis natalibus, secundum systema sexuale digestas",eng,North America (PRESENT); Altay; Austria; Belarus; Bulgaria; Central European Russia; Chita; Czechia-Slovakia; East European Russia; France; Germany; Hungary; Italy; Kazakhstan; Krasnoyarsk; Krym; NW. Balkan Pen.; New York (INTRODUCED); North Caucasus; Poland,,Adonis vernalis,"Adonis vernalis, known variously as pheasant's eye, spring pheasant's eye, yellow pheasant's eye and false hellebore, is a perennial flowering plant in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae. It is found in dry meadows and steppes in Eurasia. More specifically, this plant grows in a wide range of locations which include open forests, forest clearings, dry meadows, mesic steppe, and mostly calcareous soil. Isolated populations are found from Spain in the west across Central Europe with fine examples in Valais, Switzerland, and southern Europe, reaching southern Sweden in the north and Abruzzo in the south, with its main area of distribution being the Pannonian Basin and the West Siberian Plain. In contrast to most other European Adonis species, the flowers appear in springtime, and are up to 80 mm (3.1 in) in diameter, with up to 20 bright yellow petals. Not only do the flowers begin to grow, but so do the plants aerial organs, from around April to May.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adonis_vernalis,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Adonis+vernalis,"2. Adonis flore dodecapetalo, fructu ovato. Adonis radice perenni. Hort. cliff. 231. Fl. suec. 456. It. oel. 73. Roy. lugdb. 488. Sauv. monsp. 253. Helleborus niger tenuifolius, buphthalmi flore. Bauh. pin. 186. Buphthalmum. Dod. pempt. 261.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 577
