605,Crotalaria retusa L.,Crotalaria retusa,Crotalaria,Fabaceae,retusa,L.,,Not assessed,2942610,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Crotalaria retusa,https://www.gbif.org/species/2942610,Big Yellow Popbush; devil-bean; rattlebox; Rattlepod; Rattleweed; wedge-leaf crotalaria; wedge-leaf rattlepod; yellow rattlebox,"Note: Ali (in Nasir & Ali, Fl. W. Pakistan 100: 49. 1977) indicated four collections in the Hermann herbarium (BM) as syntypes but gave no indication of intending to typify the name.",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part C),eng,Galápagos Islands (PRESENT); Rionegro; Núcleo Aceites S.A.; Parque Nacional Natural Chingaza | Parque Nacional Natural Los Katíos (NATURALISED); Manaure | Riohacha; Complejo Humedales Hato Corozal. Cienaga Zapatosa; Caribbean (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Andaman Is. (INTRODUCED); Angola (INTRODUCED); Aruba (INTRODUCED); Assam; Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh; Belize (INTRODUCED); Benin (INTRODUCED); Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Bismarck Archipelago; Borneo,"lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva"",""Subarbusto""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica"",""Carrasco"",""Cerrado (lato sensu)"",""Restinga""]}; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial",Crotalaria retusa,"Crotalaria retusa is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by various common names including devil-bean, rattleweed, shack shack, and wedge-leaf rattlepod. It is poisonous to livestock, and contaminates human food. Its original native range is unclear, probably including tropical Asia, Africa and Australia. It has been introduced as a crop plant in many tropical areas and has escaped from cultivation to become a troublesome weed; it is listed as a noxious weed in several US states, Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, and is listed as an invasive weed in India, Cuba, and Cocos Island. Unlike some other species of Crotalaria, it is an annual plant.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crotalaria_retusa,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Crotalaria+retusa,"Note: Ali (in Nasir & Ali, Fl. W. Pakistan 100: 49. 1977) indicated four collections in the Hermann herbarium (BM) as syntypes but gave no indication of intending to typify the name.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 605
