Wikipedia summary: Crotalaria retusa is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by various common names including devil-bean, rattleweed, shack shack, and wedge-leaf rattlepod. It is poisonous to livestock, and contaminates human food. Its original native range is unclear, probably including tropical Asia, Africa and Australia. It has been introduced as a crop plant in many tropical areas and has escaped from cultivation to become a troublesome weed; it is listed as a noxious weed in several US states, Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, and is listed as an invasive weed in India, Cuba, and Cocos Island. Unlike some other species of Crotalaria, it is an annual plant.
Distribution: Galápagos Islands (PRESENT); Rionegro; Núcleo Aceites S.A.; Parque Nacional Natural Chingaza | Parque Nacional Natural Los Katíos (NATURALISED); Manaure | Riohacha; Complejo Humedales Hato Corozal. Cienaga Zapatosa; Caribbean (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Andaman Is. (INTRODUCED); Angola (INTRODUCED); Aruba (INTRODUCED); Assam; Bahamas (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh; Belize (INTRODUCED); Benin (INTRODUCED); Bermuda (INTRODUCED); Bismarck Archipelago; Borneo
