619,Cucumis melo L.,Cucumis melo,Cucumis,Cucurbitaceae,cylindrica,L.,,Not assessed,2874570,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Cucumis melo,https://www.gbif.org/species/2874570,Cantaloupe; Hami melon; honeydew; Melon; Melons; musk melon; muskmelon; Oriental melon; Rock melon,"Lectotype (Jeffrey, Cucurbitaceae Eastern Asia: 20. 1980): [icon] "" Melo variegatus, Aurantii figura, odoratissimus "" in Dillenius, Hort. Eltham. 2: 223, t. 177, f. 218. 1732. - Typotype: Herb. Dillenius (OXF).",Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part C),eng,"Galápagos Islands (PRESENT); Bucaramanga; Distrito Regional de Manejo Integrado (DRMI) Laguna de Sonso, municipio de Guadalajara de Buga, Valle del Cauca, Colombia; Complejo Humedales Hato Corozal. Cienaga Zapatosa; Africa (PRESENT); Caribbean (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Southern Asia (PRESENT); Afghanistan; Alabama (INTRODUCED); Albania (INTRODUCED); Algeria (INTRODUCED); Andaman Is. (INTRODUCED); Angola; Argentina Northeast (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northwest (INTRODUCED); Arizona (INTRODUCED); Arkansas (INTRODUCED); Assam (INTRODUCED); Austria (INTRODUCED)","lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Liana/volúvel/trepadeira""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial",Cucumis melo,"Cucumis melo, also known as melon or true melon, is a species of Cucumis that has been developed into many cultivated varieties. The fruit is a pepo. The flesh is either sweet or bland, with or without an aroma, and the rind can be smooth, ribbed, wrinkled, or netted. The species is sometimes referred to as muskmelon. However, there is no consensus about the usage of this term, as it can also be used as a specific name for the musky netted-rind American cantaloupe, or as a generic name for any sweet-flesh variety such the inodorous smooth-rind honeydew melon.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cucumis_melo,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Cucumis+melo,"Lectotype (Jeffrey, Cucurbitaceae Eastern Asia: 20. 1980): [icon] "" Melo variegatus, Aurantii figura, odoratissimus "" in Dillenius, Hort. Eltham. 2: 223, t. 177, f. 218. 1732. - Typotype: Herb. Dillenius (OXF).",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 619
