632,Anthurium crystallinum Linden & André,Anthurium crystallinum,Anthurium,Araceae,crystallinum,Linden & André,,Not assessed,2872232,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Anthurium crystallinum,https://www.gbif.org/species/2872232,Crystal Anthurium; scalloped laceleaf,Es nativo de América Tropical; se conoce en el departamento de Antioquia mas especificamente en el Municipio de San Luis y Nariño,Plantas priorizadas para la conservación en la Región del Eje Cafetero,,"Floridablanca; Cuenca de Río Claro; Colombia; Panamá; BR (MANAGED); La Habana | Cundinamarca | Antioquia | Caldas | Tolima | Santander | Quindío | Chocó | Risaralda; Antioquia, Chocó, Risaralda, Tolima (NATIVE); CO (NATIVE); DZ (PRESENT); SC (PRESENT); TW (INTRODUCED)","habitat: terrestrial; habitat: Terrestrial; lifeForm: Hierba, Epífita; habitat: Garden, lifeForm: Ht|ground herbs|Ht|Strates inférieures (understorey) [Inf]; lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva"",""Subarbusto""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}; lifeForm: Hierba | Epífita",Anthurium crystallinum,"Anthurium crystallinum is a species of flowering plant in the family Araceae, native to rainforest margins in Colombia and Panama. Growing to around 90 cm (35 in) tall and wide, A. crystallinum is an epiphytic perennial evergreen, known for its dark green and velvety-textured, heart-shaped leaves featuring prominent white veining, and somewhat resembles a smaller version of Anthurium magnificum. The inflorescence is a somewhat visually-undistinguished spathe with a pale green spadix, appearing throughout the year.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthurium_crystallinum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Anthurium+crystallinum,Es nativo de América Tropical; se conoce en el departamento de Antioquia mas especificamente en el Municipio de San Luis y Nariño,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 632
