Wikipedia summary: Cirsium foliosum , also called leafy thistle, foliose thistle, elk thistle, or Evert's thistle, is a North American plant species in the tribe Cardueae within the family Asteraceae. The species is native to Alaska, Yukon, Northwest Territories, Alberta, British Columbia, and Wyoming.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Alberta; British Columbia; Northwest Territories; Wyoming; Yukon; Mexico (PRESENT); Idaho (PRESENT); Montana (PRESENT); Oregon (PRESENT); Washington (PRESENT); Alberta (PRESENT); Alaska (PRESENT); British Columbia (PRESENT); Northwest Territories (PRESENT); Wyoming (PRESENT); Yukon (PRESENT); Canada (Alberta, British Columbia, N. W. T., Yukon); USA (Wyoming); Quebec (EXCLUDED); Saskatchewan (EXCLUDED)
