Wikipedia summary: Comptonia peregrina is a species of flowering plant in the family Myricaceae native to eastern North America. It is the only extant (living) species in the genus Comptonia, although some extinct species are placed in the genus.
Distribution: North America (PRESENT); Connecticut; Delaware; Georgia; Illinois; Indiana; Kentucky; Maine; Maryland; Massachusetts; Michigan; Minnesota; New Brunswick; New Hampshire; New Jersey; New York; North Carolina; Nova Scotia; Ohio; Ontario
