708,Conoclinium coelestinum (L.) DC.,Conoclinium coelestinum,Conoclinium,Asteraceae,coelestinum,(L.) DC.,,Not assessed,3090343,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Conoclinium coelestinum,https://www.gbif.org/species/3090343,blue boneset; blue mist-flower; blue mistflower; mistflower; Perennial ageratum,Lectotype (Reveal & al. in Huntia 7: 221. 1987): Herb. Linn. No. 978.20 (LINN).,Chapter 7: Linnaean Plant Names and their Types (part E),eng,North America (PRESENT); Alabama; Arkansas; China South-Central (INTRODUCED); Cuba; Delaware; Florida; Georgia; Germany (INTRODUCED); Illinois; Indiana; India (INTRODUCED); Kansas; Kentucky; Louisiana; Maryland; Michigan; Mississippi; Missouri; Nebraska,habitat: Terrestrial,Conoclinium coelestinum,"Conoclinium coelestinum, commonly known as blue mistflower, mistflower, wild ageratum, or blue boneset, is a North American species of herbaceous perennial flowering plant in the family Asteraceae. It was formerly classified in the genus Eupatorium, but phylogenetic analyses in the late 20th century research indicated that that genus should be split, and the species was reclassified in Conoclinium.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conoclinium_coelestinum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Conoclinium+coelestinum,Lectotype (Reveal & al. in Huntia 7: 221. 1987): Herb. Linn. No. 978.20 (LINN).,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 708
