728,Maianthemum canadense Desf.,Maianthemum canadense,Maianthemum,Asparagaceae,canadense,Desf.,,Not assessed,2769544,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Maianthemum canadense,https://www.gbif.org/species/2769544,Canada beadruby; Canada Mayflower; Canadian May lily; Canadian May-lily; Canadian Mayflower; false lily of the valley; False Lily-of-the-valley; Two-leaf-solomon's-seal; Two-leaved Solomon's Seal; two-leaved Solomon's-seal; wild lily of the valley; Wild Lily-of-the-valley,herb,Database of Vascular Plants of Canada (VASCAN),,North America (PRESENT); Alberta; British Columbia; Connecticut; Delaware; District of Columbia; Georgia; Illinois; Indiana; Iowa; Kentucky; Labrador; Maine; Manitoba; Maryland; Massachusetts; Michigan; Minnesota; Montana; Nebraska,,Maianthemum canadense,"Maianthemum canadense is an understory perennial flowering plant, native to Canada and the northeastern United States, from Yukon and British Columbia east to Newfoundland, into St. Pierre and Miquelon. It can be found growing in both coniferous and deciduous forests. The plant appears in two forms, either as a single leaf rising from the ground with no fruiting structures or as a flowering/fruiting stem with two to three leaves. Flowering shoots have clusters of 12–25 starry-shaped, white flowers held above the leaves.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maianthemum_canadense,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Maianthemum+canadense,herb,GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 728
