Wikipedia summary: Cerbera manghas, commonly known as the sea mango, wawai, pink-eyed cerbera, tangena or bintaro is a small evergreen coastal tree growing up to 12 metres (39 ft) tall. It is native to coastal areas in Africa, Asia, Australasia, and the Pacific islands. It is classified as one of the three species in the genus Cerbera that constitute mangroves. Despite its name, it is not closely related to the mango.
Distribution: Bangladesh; Bismarck Archipelago; Borneo; Cambodia; Caroline Is.; Chagos Archipelago (INTRODUCED); China Southeast; Christmas I.; Comoros; Fiji; Gilbert Is.; Hainan; India; Jawa; Laos; Lesser Sunda Is.; Madagascar; Malaya; Maluku; Marquesas
