798,Nothofagus alpina (Poepp. & Endl.) Oerst.,Nothofagus alpina,Nothofagus,Nothofagaceae,alpina,(Poepp. & Endl.) Oerst.,,LC,2874878,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Nothofagus alpina,https://www.gbif.org/species/2874878,rauli; rauli beech,,,,Argentina South; Chile Central; Chile South; Germany (INTRODUCED); Great Britain (INTRODUCED); Ireland (INTRODUCED); Global (PRESENT); GB (PRESENT),habitat: Terrestrial,Nothofagus alpina,"Nothofagus alpina, also called raulí or raulí beech, is a species of plant in the Nothofagaceae family. A deciduous tree, it grows in Chile and Argentina, reaching 50 m (160 ft) in height and more than 2 m (6.6 ft) in diameter. It is distributed from 35–42° south latitude. It is found in the Andes. It tolerates low temperatures and heavy winds. It has a straight and cylindrical trunk with grey bark.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nothofagus_alpina,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Nothofagus+alpina,"Nothofagus alpina, also called raulí or raulí beech, is a species of plant in the Nothofagaceae family. A deciduous tree, it grows in Chile and Argentina, reaching 50 m (160 ft) in height and more than 2 m (6.6 ft) in diameter. It is distributed from 35–42° south latitude. It is found in the Andes. It tolerates low temperatures and heavy winds. It has a straight and cylindrical trunk with grey bark.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 798
