Wikipedia summary: Nothofagus alpina, also called raulí or raulí beech, is a species of plant in the Nothofagaceae family. A deciduous tree, it grows in Chile and Argentina, reaching 50 m (160 ft) in height and more than 2 m (6.6 ft) in diameter. It is distributed from 35–42° south latitude. It is found in the Andes. It tolerates low temperatures and heavy winds. It has a straight and cylindrical trunk with grey bark.
Distribution: Argentina South; Chile Central; Chile South; Germany (INTRODUCED); Great Britain (INTRODUCED); Ireland (INTRODUCED); Global (PRESENT); GB (PRESENT)
