799,Nothofagus pumilio (Poepp. & Endl.) Krasser,Nothofagus pumilio,Nothofagus,Nothofagaceae,pumilio,(Poepp. & Endl.) Krasser,,LC,2874907,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Nothofagus pumilio,https://www.gbif.org/species/2874907,Lenga Beech,,,,"Argentina South; Chile Central; Chile South; Global (PRESENT); Argentina (Chubut, Neuquen, Rio Negro, Santa Cruz, Tierra del Fuego); Chile (Maule, Ñuble, Biobío, Araucanía, Los Rios, Los Lagos, Aisén, Magallanes)",,Nothofagus pumilio,"Nothofagus pumilio, the lenga beech, is a deciduous tree or shrub in the Nothofagaceae family that is native to the southern Andes range, in the temperate forests of Chile and Argentina to Tierra del Fuego, from 35° to 56° South latitude. This tree is in the same genus as the coihue. It regenerates easily after fires. The wood is of good quality, moderate durability, and is easy to work with. It is used in furniture, shingles and construction and sometimes as a substitute for American black cherry in the manufacturing of cabinets.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nothofagus_pumilio,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Nothofagus+pumilio,"Nothofagus pumilio, the lenga beech, is a deciduous tree or shrub in the Nothofagaceae family that is native to the southern Andes range, in the temperate forests of Chile and Argentina to Tierra del Fuego, from 35° to 56° South latitude. This tree is in the same genus as the coihue. It regenerates easily after fires. The wood is of good quality, moderate durability, and is easy to work with. It is used in furniture, shingles and construction and sometimes as a substitute for American black cherry in the manufacturing of cabinets.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 799
