Wikipedia summary: Dacrycarpus kinabaluensis is a species of shrubby conifer in the family Podocarpaceae. It is a shrubby tree found only on Mount Kinabalu in Sabah, Malaysian Borneo.
Distribution: Assam; Bangladesh; Borneo; Cambodia; Caroline Is.; China Southeast; Hainan; Jawa; Laos; Lesser Sunda Is.; Madagascar; Malaya; Maluku; Myanmar; New Caledonia; New Guinea; Philippines; Queensland; Seychelles; Sri Lanka
