Wikipedia summary: Aphelandra sinclairiana is a plant species commonly called coral aphelandra, orange shrimp plant, Panama queen or Sinclair's aphelandra. It is a shrub up to 3 m high, native to Central America, specifically Panama, Costa Rica, Honduras and Nicaragua. It is also cultivated in warm locations elsewhere, with pink, red, orange, or red-violet flowers and bracts.
Distribution: Costa Rica; Honduras; Nicaragua; Panamá; Society Isl. [I] (Tahiti [I]); Honduras [c]; Nicaragua; Costa Rica; Panama; BR (MANAGED); CU (PRESENT); CU (INTRODUCED); TW (INTRODUCED)
