828,Hypericum revolutum Vahl,Hypericum revolutum,Hypericum,Hypericaceae,revolutum,Vahl,,LC,7330049,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Hypericum revolutum,https://www.gbif.org/species/7330049,Curry Bush; currybush; forest-primrose,,,,Burundi; Cameroon; Cape Provinces; Congo; DR Congo; Eritrea; Eswatini; Ethiopia; Gulf of Guinea Is.; Kenya; KwaZulu-Natal; Malawi; Mozambique; Nigeria; Northern Provinces; Rwanda; Saudi Arabia; Sudan-South Sudan; Tanzania; Uganda,,Hypericum revolutum,"Hypericum revolutum is a shrub or small tree in the genus Hypericum native to Arabia and Africa. It is evergreen, with leaves opposite, closely spaced and crowded at the ends of branches, c. 20 × 5 mm, green to slightly glaucous, sessile, clasping at the base. Single bright yellow flowers form at the ends of branches, up to 5 cm in diameter, blooming from June to November. Fruit is a reddish-brown capsule, up to 13 × 10 mm.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypericum_revolutum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Hypericum+revolutum,"Hypericum revolutum is a shrub or small tree in the genus Hypericum native to Arabia and Africa. It is evergreen, with leaves opposite, closely spaced and crowded at the ends of branches, c. 20 × 5 mm, green to slightly glaucous, sessile, clasping at the base. Single bright yellow flowers form at the ends of branches, up to 5 cm in diameter, blooming from June to November. Fruit is a reddish-brown capsule, up to 13 × 10 mm.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 828
