Wikipedia summary: Vachellia farnesiana, also known as Acacia farnesiana, and previously Mimosa farnesiana, commonly known as sweet acacia, huisache, casha tree, or needle bush, is a species of shrub or small tree in the legume family, Fabaceae. Its flowers are used in the perfume industry.
Distribution: Aratoca | Barichara | Bucaramanga | Capitanejo | Cepitá | Concepción | Enciso | Girón | Piedecuesta | Piedecuesta | Pinchote | San José de Miranda | Villanueva; Distrito Regional de Manejo Integrado (DRMI) Laguna de Sonso, municipio de Guadalajara de Buga, Valle del Cauca, Colombia; SFF Iguaque; Municipio de Barrancas, Cerrejón Cerro La Potrosa, Bosque Seco Tropical del caribe colombiano, lat: 11° 05' 5.1'' N, long: 72° 33' 57.8'' W, 206-259 m; Paz de Río; Caribbean (PRESENT); North America (PRESENT); Oceania (PRESENT); Alabama; Algeria (INTRODUCED); Andaman Is. (INTRODUCED); Angola (INTRODUCED); Argentina Northeast; Arizona; Arkansas; Ascension (INTRODUCED); Assam (INTRODUCED); Bahamas; Baleares (INTRODUCED); Bangladesh (INTRODUCED)
