Wikipedia summary: Crotalaria laburnifolia, called the rattle pod, is a highly variable species of flowering plant in the genus Crotalaria, widely distributed in central, eastern and southern Africa, the Seychelles, the Indian Subcontinent, Thailand, the Lesser Sunda Islands, Java, and Queensland in Australia. It has been introduced into Western Australia. It has gained the Royal Horticultural Society's Award of Garden Merit.
