842,Schinopsis balansae Engl.,Schinopsis balansae,Schinopsis,Anacardiaceae,balansae,Engl.,,LR/lc,3190533,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Schinopsis balansae,https://www.gbif.org/species/3190533,quebracho; Red Quebracho; willow-leaf red quebracho,"Voucher: M. Peña-Chocarro et al. 2284 (BM, CTES, FCQ, G, MO, PY, SI, UNR).","Checklist of vascular plants of the Ñeembucú Department, Paraguay",,"Argentina Northeast; Brazil West-Central; Paraguay; Global (PRESENT); WC-Brazil (Mato Grosso); Paraguay (Alto Paraguay, Alto Paraná, Concepcion, Neembucu, Paraguari, Pres. Hayes, San Pedro); Argentina (Chaco, Corrientes, Entre Rios, Formosa, Santiago del Estero, Santa Fe); BR (NATIVE)","lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Árvore""],""habitat"":[""Terrícola""],""vegetationType"":[""Floresta Estacional Semidecidual""]}",Schinopsis balansae,"Schinopsis balansae is a hardwood tree known as willow-leaf red quebracho which forms forests in the subtropical Humid Chaco ecoregion of north-eastern Argentina, and Paraguay. It is also found in the wild Pantanal vegetation in Brazil. Some of its vernacular names are quebracho colorado chaqueño and quebracho santafesino. Other species, like Schinopsis lorentzii, bear the general name quebracho and have similar properties and uses. S. balansae shares its habitat with a species of the same genus, S. heterophylla, and the two are often confused.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schinopsis_balansae,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Schinopsis+balansae,"Voucher: M. Peña-Chocarro et al. 2284 (BM, CTES, FCQ, G, MO, PY, SI, UNR).",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 842
Scientific name: Schinopsis balansae
Full species name: Schinopsis balansae Engl.
Genus: Schinopsis
Family: Anacardiaceae
IUCN status: LR/lc
Accepted scientific name: Schinopsis balansae
Common names: quebracho; Red Quebracho; willow-leaf red quebracho
GBIF description: Voucher: M. Peña-Chocarro et al. 2284 (BM, CTES, FCQ, G, MO, PY, SI, UNR).
Wikipedia summary: Schinopsis balansae is a hardwood tree known as willow-leaf red quebracho which forms forests in the subtropical Humid Chaco ecoregion of north-eastern Argentina, and Paraguay. It is also found in the wild Pantanal vegetation in Brazil. Some of its vernacular names are quebracho colorado chaqueño and quebracho santafesino. Other species, like Schinopsis lorentzii, bear the general name quebracho and have similar properties and uses. S. balansae shares its habitat with a species of the same genus, S. heterophylla, and the two are often confused.
Distribution: Argentina Northeast; Brazil West-Central; Paraguay; Global (PRESENT); WC-Brazil (Mato Grosso); Paraguay (Alto Paraguay, Alto Paraná, Concepcion, Neembucu, Paraguari, Pres. Hayes, San Pedro); Argentina (Chaco, Corrientes, Entre Rios, Formosa, Santiago del Estero, Santa Fe); BR (NATIVE)
