905,Trachelospermum asiaticum (Siebold & Zucc.) Nakai,Trachelospermum asiaticum,Trachelospermum,Apocynaceae,asiaticum,(Siebold & Zucc.) Nakai,,Not assessed,7317060,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Trachelospermum asiaticum,https://www.gbif.org/species/7317060,Asian jasmine; Asian-jasmine; Asiatic jasmine,,,,"Arkansas (INTRODUCED); Assam; Bangladesh; Borneo; China South-Central; China Southeast; Hainan; India; Japan; Korea; Laos; Malaya; Myanmar; Nansei-shoto; Ogasawara-shoto; Taiwan; Thailand; Tibet; Vietnam; Tibet; South Korea; Japan (Honshu, Shikoku, Kyushu); Ryukyu Isl.; India (Meghalaya, Nagaland); Bangladesh; Myanmar; Thailand; Laos; Vietnam; peninsular Malaysia (Perak, Pahang); Borneo",,Trachelospermum asiaticum,"Trachelospermum asiaticum, the Asiatic jasmine, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apocynaceae and it is native to Asia. Its flowers resemble stars, so it is also referred to as yellow star jasmine or Asian star jasmine. This is a fast growing evergreen vine, often used to cover fences, walls, and similar surfaces. It is heat- and cold- tolerant, and grows even in shady areas.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trachelospermum_asiaticum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Trachelospermum+asiaticum,"Trachelospermum asiaticum, the Asiatic jasmine, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apocynaceae and it is native to Asia. Its flowers resemble stars, so it is also referred to as yellow star jasmine or Asian star jasmine. This is a fast growing evergreen vine, often used to cover fences, walls, and similar surfaces. It is heat- and cold- tolerant, and grows even in shady areas.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 905
