Wikipedia summary: Alocasia lauterbachiana, the purple sword, silver sword, or baroque sword, is a species of flowering plant in the family Araceae, native to northern New Guinea and the Bismarck Archipelago. With its upward-pointing leaves reaching 1.5 m (5 ft), it is kept as a houseplant and is readily available in commerce.
Distribution: Bismarck Archipelago; New Guinea
Sources: https://www.gbif.org/species/5329877 | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alocasia_lauterbachiana | https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Alocasia+lauterbachiana",ok
908,Alocasia reginula A.Hay,Alocasia reginula,Alocasia,Araceae,reginula,A.Hay,,Not assessed,5329895,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Alocasia reginula,https://www.gbif.org/species/5329895,Black Velvet Alocasia,,,,Borneo,,Alocasia reginula,"Alocasia reginula, black velvet, is a species of flowering cormous aroid, native to Sabah state in Malaysia. This plant, often referred to as one of the ""jewel"" Alocasias, became increasingly popular among plant hobbyists between the years 2018 to 2020. Until as recently as 2021 though, not much was known about the plant or its origins. Originally described from cultivation, and often sold as “Alocasia 'Black Velvet'”, it is not a modern cultivar or hybrid; A. reginula is its own natural species. It is only known from dry, deeply shaded limestone cliffs in Tabin Wildlife Reserve. As a houseplant it needs sharp drainage or it will very likely rot.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alocasia_reginula,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Alocasia+reginula,"Alocasia reginula, black velvet, is a species of flowering cormous aroid, native to Sabah state in Malaysia. This plant, often referred to as one of the ""jewel"" Alocasias, became increasingly popular among plant hobbyists between the years 2018 to 2020. Until as recently as 2021 though, not much was known about the plant or its origins. Originally described from cultivation, and often sold as “Alocasia 'Black Velvet'”, it is not a modern cultivar or hybrid; A. reginula is its own natural species. It is only known from dry, deeply shaded limestone cliffs in Tabin Wildlife Reserve. As a houseplant it needs sharp drainage or it will very likely rot.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 908
Scientific name: Alocasia reginula
Full species name: Alocasia reginula A.Hay
Genus: Alocasia
Family: Araceae
IUCN status: Not assessed
Accepted scientific name: Alocasia reginula
Common names: Black Velvet Alocasia
Wikipedia summary: Alocasia reginula, black velvet, is a species of flowering cormous aroid, native to Sabah state in Malaysia. This plant, often referred to as one of the ""jewel"" Alocasias, became increasingly popular among plant hobbyists between the years 2018 to 2020. Until as recently as 2021 though, not much was known about the plant or its origins. Originally described from cultivation, and often sold as “Alocasia 'Black Velvet'”, it is not a modern cultivar or hybrid; A. reginula is its own natural species. It is only known from dry, deeply shaded limestone cliffs in Tabin Wildlife Reserve. As a houseplant it needs sharp drainage or it will very likely rot.
Distribution: Borneo
Sources: https://www.gbif.org/species/5329895 | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alocasia_reginula | https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Alocasia+reginula",ok
