34(47) cm long, 4-15 mm diam. near base, 2-7 mm diam. near apex; flowers rhombic, 2.4-2.5 mm in both directions, the sides straight to sigmoid; 6-8 flowers visible in principal spiral, 4-12 in alternate spiral; tepals matte; lateral tepals 1.2-1.3 mm wide, the inner margins broadly rounded; pistils emergent but not raised, green; stigma linear to oblong-ellipsoid, 0.6-0.9 mm long; stamens emerging from the base in a slow, regular progression; anthers orange to pale yellow to creamy white, ca. 1 mm long, 0.9 mm wide, held at edge of tepals and inclined over pistil; thecae ellipsoid; pollen pale yellow-orange fading to white. INFRUCTESCENCE with spadix to 60 cm long; berries red, oblong-ellipsoid, rounded at apex, 10- 15 mm long; mesocarp transparent, gelatinous; seeds 2 per berry, oblong, flattened, ca. 3-5 mm long.",GBIF,"PlantNet species_id: 913
