926,Maytenus ilicifolia Mart. ex Reissek,Maytenus ilicifolia,Maytenus,Celastraceae,ilicifolia,Mart. ex Reissek,,Not assessed,7265474,HIGHERRANK,99,ACCEPTED,Monteverdia,https://www.gbif.org/species/7265474,,,,,,,Maytenus,"Maytenus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Celastraceae. Members of the genus are distributed throughout Central and South America, Southeast Asia, Micronesia, and Australasia, the Indian Ocean and Africa. They grow in a very wide variety of climates, from tropical to subpolar. The traditional circumscription of Maytenus was paraphyletic, so many species have been transferred to Denhamia and Gymnosporia.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maytenus,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Maytenus+ilicifolia,"Maytenus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Celastraceae. Members of the genus are distributed throughout Central and South America, Southeast Asia, Micronesia, and Australasia, the Indian Ocean and Africa. They grow in a very wide variety of climates, from tropical to subpolar. The traditional circumscription of Maytenus was paraphyletic, so many species have been transferred to Denhamia and Gymnosporia.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 926
