967,Dendrobium kingianum Bidwill ex Lindl.,Dendrobium kingianum,Dendrobium,Orchidaceae,kingianum,Bidwill ex Lindl.,,Not assessed,5316009,EXACT,99,ACCEPTED,Dendrobium kingianum,https://www.gbif.org/species/5316009,pink rock orchid,,,,New South Wales; New Zealand North (INTRODUCED); Queensland; BR (MANAGED),"lifeForm: {""lifeForm"":[""Erva""],""habitat"":[""Epífita""],""vegetationType"":[""Área Antrópica""]}",Dendrobium kingianum,"Dendrobium kingianum, commonly known as the pink rock orchid, is a flowering plant in the orchid family Orchidaceae and is endemic to eastern Australia. It usually grows on rocks, rarely as an epiphyte, and has thin, spreading leaves and spikes of up to fifteen, usually pink flowers in late winter to spring. It is popular in Australian native horticulture and is a commonly cultivated orchid among Australian orchid species growers.",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dendrobium_kingianum,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Dendrobium+kingianum,"Dendrobium kingianum, commonly known as the pink rock orchid, is a flowering plant in the orchid family Orchidaceae and is endemic to eastern Australia. It usually grows on rocks, rarely as an epiphyte, and has thin, spreading leaves and spikes of up to fifteen, usually pink flowers in late winter to spring. It is popular in Australian native horticulture and is a commonly cultivated orchid among Australian orchid species growers.",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 967
Scientific name: Dendrobium kingianum
Full species name: Dendrobium kingianum Bidwill ex Lindl.
