986,Eriocapitella tomentosa (Maxim.) Christenh. & Byng,Eriocapitella tomentosa,Eriocapitella,Ranunculaceae,tomentosa,(Maxim.) Christenh. & Byng,,Not assessed,9675867,EXACT,100,ACCEPTED,Eriocapitella tomentosa,https://www.gbif.org/species/9675867,Grape-leaved Anemone; Hardy Grape Leaf Anemone,,,,"China North-Central; China South-Central; China Southeast; Myanmar; Qinghai; China (W-Hebei, W-Henan, W-Hubei, E-Qinghai, Shaanxi, Shanxi, W-Sichuan); Belgium (PRESENT); Flemish Region (PRESENT); NO (PRESENT)",,Eriocapitella tomentosa,"Eriocapitella tomentosa, a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae, is native to Asia. The specific epithet tomentosa means ""thickly matted with hairs, tomentum (padding)"". It was formerly a member of genus Anemone and shares the common name Japanese anemone with several other Eriocapitella species. In Chinese, a common name is dàhuǒcǎo (大火草), which literally means ""big fire grass"" or ""great fireweed"".",https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eriocapitella_tomentosa,https://powo.science.kew.org/results?q=Eriocapitella+tomentosa,"Eriocapitella tomentosa, a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae, is native to Asia. The specific epithet tomentosa means ""thickly matted with hairs, tomentum (padding)"". It was formerly a member of genus Anemone and shares the common name Japanese anemone with several other Eriocapitella species. In Chinese, a common name is dàhuǒcǎo (大火草), which literally means ""big fire grass"" or ""great fireweed"".",Wikipedia-en,"PlantNet species_id: 986
