Wikipedia summary: Eriocapitella tomentosa, a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family Ranunculaceae, is native to Asia. The specific epithet tomentosa means ""thickly matted with hairs, tomentum (padding)"". It was formerly a member of genus Anemone and shares the common name Japanese anemone with several other Eriocapitella species. In Chinese, a common name is dàhuǒcǎo (大火草), which literally means ""big fire grass"" or ""great fireweed"".
Distribution: China North-Central; China South-Central; China Southeast; Myanmar; Qinghai; China (W-Hebei, W-Henan, W-Hubei, E-Qinghai, Shaanxi, Shanxi, W-Sichuan); Belgium (PRESENT); Flemish Region (PRESENT); NO (PRESENT)
