Wikipedia summary: Nepenthes truncata is a tropical pitcher plant endemic to the Philippines. It is known from the islands of Dinagat, Leyte, and Mindanao. The species grows at an elevation of 0–1,500 m above sea level. Nepenthes truncata is characterised by its heart-shaped (truncate) leaves and very large pitchers, which can reach up to 40 cm in height.
Distribution: Southern Asia (PRESENT); Philippines; Global (PRESENT); Philippines (Mindanao, Dinagat)
